v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

97// static
98Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::HasProperty(LookupIterator* it) {
99 for (;; it->Next()) {
100 switch (it->state()) {
101 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
102 UNREACHABLE();
103 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
104 return JSProxy::HasProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
105 it->GetName());
106 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
107 return Just(false);
108 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
109 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> result =
110 JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptor(it);
111 if (result.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
112 if (result.FromJust() != ABSENT) return Just(true);
113 continue;
114 }
115 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK: {
116 if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
117 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> result =
118 JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithFailedAccessCheck(it);
119 if (result.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
120 return Just(result.FromJust() != ABSENT);
121 }
122 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
123 // TypedArray out-of-bounds access.
124 return Just(false);
125 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
126 case LookupIterator::DATA:
127 return Just(true);
128 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
129 return Just(false);
130 }
131 UNREACHABLE();
132 }
133}
134
135// static
136Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::HasOwnProperty(Isolate* isolate,
137 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
138 DirectHandle<Name> name) {
139 if (IsJSModuleNamespace(*object)) {
140 PropertyDescriptor desc;
141 return JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, object, name, &desc);
142 }
143
144 if (IsJSObject(*object)) { // Shortcut.
145 PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
146 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN);
147 return HasProperty(&it);
148 }
149
150 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> attributes =
151 JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyAttributes(isolate, object, name);
152 MAYBE_RETURN(attributes, Nothing<bool>());
153 return Just(attributes.FromJust() != ABSENT);
154}
155
156Handle<Object> JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(LookupIterator* it,
157 AllocationPolicy allocation_policy) {
158 for (;; it->Next()) {
159 switch (it->state()) {
160 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
161 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
162 UNREACHABLE();
163 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
164 // Support calling this method without an active context, but refuse
165 // access to access-checked objects in that case.
166 if (!it->isolate()->context().is_null() && it->HasAccess()) continue;
167 [[fallthrough]];
168 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
169 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
170 it->NotFound();
171 return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
172 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
173 // TODO(verwaest): For now this doesn't call into AccessorInfo, since
174 // clients don't need it. Update once relevant.
175 it->NotFound();
176 return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
177 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
178 return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
179 case LookupIterator::DATA:
180 return it->GetDataValue(allocation_policy);
181 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
182 return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
183 }
184 UNREACHABLE();
185 }
186}
187
188// static
189Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::HasInPrototypeChain(Isolate* isolate,
190 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
191 DirectHandle<Object> proto) {
192 PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, object, kStartAtReceiver);
193 while (true) {
194 if (!iter.AdvanceFollowingProxies()) return Nothing<bool>();
195 if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return Just(false);
196 if (PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter).is_identical_to(proto)) {
197 return Just(true);
198 }
199 }
200}
201
202// static
203Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::CheckPrivateNameStore(LookupIterator* it,
204 bool is_define) {
205 DCHECK(it->GetName()->IsPrivateName());
206 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
207 DirectHandle<String> name_string(
208 Cast<String>(Cast<Symbol>(it->GetName())->description()), isolate);
209 for (;; it->Next()) {
210 switch (it->state()) {
211 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
212 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
213 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
214 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
215 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
216 UNREACHABLE();
217 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
218 if (!it->HasAccess()) {
219 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate,
220 isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(
221 Cast<JSObject>(it->GetReceiver())),
222 Nothing<bool>());
223 UNREACHABLE();
224 }
225 continue;
226 case LookupIterator::DATA:
227 if (is_define) {
228 MessageTemplate message =
229 it->GetName()->IsPrivateBrand()
230 ? MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateBrandReinitialization
231 : MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateFieldReinitialization;
232 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate,
233 GetShouldThrow(isolate, Nothing<ShouldThrow>()),
234 NewTypeError(message, name_string, it->GetReceiver()));
235 }
236 return Just(true);
237 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
238 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
239 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
240 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
241 if (!is_define) {
242 RETURN_FAILURE(
243 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, Nothing<ShouldThrow>()),
244 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateMemberWrite,
245 name_string, it->GetReceiver()));
246 } else if (IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*it->GetReceiver())) {
247 RETURN_FAILURE(
248 isolate, kThrowOnError,
249 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed, name_string));
250 }
251 return Just(true);
252 }
253 UNREACHABLE();
254 }
255}

257namespace {
258
259bool HasExcludedProperty(base::Vector<DirectHandle<Object>> excluded_properties,
260 DirectHandle<Object> search_element) {
261 // TODO(gsathya): Change this to be a hashtable.
262 for (DirectHandle<Object> object : excluded_properties) {
263 if (Object::SameValue(*search_element, *object)) {
264 return true;
265 }
266 }
267
268 return false;
269}
270
271// If direct handles are enabled, it is the responsibility of the caller to
272// ensure that the memory pointed to by `excluded_properties` is scanned
273// during CSS, e.g., it comes from a `DirectHandleVector<Object>`.
274V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> FastAssign(
275 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target,
276 DirectHandle<Object> source, PropertiesEnumerationMode mode,
277 base::Vector<DirectHandle<Object>> excluded_properties, bool use_set) {
278 // Non-empty strings are the only non-JSReceivers that need to be handled
279 // explicitly by Object.assign.
280 if (!IsJSReceiver(*source)) {
281 return Just(!IsString(*source) || Cast<String>(*source)->length() == 0);
282 }
283
284 // If the target is deprecated, the object will be updated on first store. If
285 // the source for that store equals the target, this will invalidate the
286 // cached representation of the source. Preventively upgrade the target.
287 // Do this on each iteration since any property load could cause deprecation.
288 if (target->map()->is_deprecated()) {
289 JSObject::MigrateInstance(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(target));
290 }
291
292 DirectHandle<Map> map(Cast<JSReceiver>(*source)->map(), isolate);
293
294 if (!IsJSObjectMap(*map)) return Just(false);
295 if (!map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties()) return Just(false);
296
297 DirectHandle<JSObject> from = Cast<JSObject>(source);
298 if (from->elements() != ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array()) {
299 return Just(false);
300 }
301
302 // We should never try to copy properties from an object itself.
303 CHECK_IMPLIES(!use_set, !target.is_identical_to(from));
304
305 bool stable = true;
306
307 // Process symbols last and only do that if we found symbols.
308 bool has_symbol = false;
309 bool process_symbol_only = false;
310 while (true) {
311 for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
312 HandleScope inner_scope(isolate);
313
314 // The descriptor array is not cached on purpose since it has to stay in
315 // sync with map->instance_descriptors to avoid it from being pruned.
316 DirectHandle<Name> next_key(map->instance_descriptors(isolate)->GetKey(i),
317 isolate);
318 if (mode == PropertiesEnumerationMode::kEnumerationOrder) {
319 if (IsSymbol(*next_key)) {
320 has_symbol = true;
321 if (!process_symbol_only) continue;
322 } else {
323 if (process_symbol_only) continue;
324 }
325 }
326 DirectHandle<Object> prop_value;
327 // Directly decode from the descriptor array if |from| did not change
328 // shape.
329 if (stable) {
330 DCHECK_EQ(from->map(), *map);
331
332 PropertyDetails details =
333 map->instance_descriptors(isolate)->GetDetails(i);
334 if (!details.IsEnumerable()) continue;
335 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
336 CHECK_EQ(details.location(), PropertyLocation::kField);
337 Representation representation = details.representation();
338 FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(
339 *map, details.field_index(), representation);
340 prop_value =
341 JSObject::FastPropertyAt(isolate, from, representation, index);
342 } else {
343 LookupIterator it(isolate, from, next_key,
344 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
345 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
346 isolate, prop_value, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
347 stable = from->map() == *map;
348 }
349 } else {
350 // If the map did change, do a slower lookup. We are still guaranteed
351 // that the object has a simple shape, and that the key is a name.
352 LookupIterator it(isolate, from, next_key, from,
353 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
354 if (!it.IsFound()) continue;
355 DCHECK(it.state() == LookupIterator::DATA ||
356 it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESSOR);
357 if (!it.IsEnumerable()) continue;
358 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
359 isolate, prop_value, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
360 }
361
362 if (use_set) {
363 // The lookup will walk the prototype chain, so we have to be careful
364 // to treat any key correctly for any receiver/holder.
365 PropertyKey key(isolate, next_key);
366 LookupIterator it(isolate, target, key);
367 Maybe<bool> result =
368 Object::SetProperty(&it, prop_value, StoreOrigin::kNamed,
369 Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError));
370 if (result.IsNothing()) return result;
371 if (stable) {
372 stable = from->map() == *map;
373 }
374 } else {
375 // No element indexes should get here or the exclusion check may
376 // yield false negatives for type mismatch.
377 if (!excluded_properties.empty() &&
378 HasExcludedProperty(excluded_properties, next_key)) {
379 continue;
380 }
381
382 // 4a ii 2. Perform ? CreateDataProperty(target, nextKey, propValue).
383 // This is an OWN lookup, so constructing a named-mode LookupIterator
384 // from {next_key} is safe.
385 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, target, next_key,
386 prop_value, Just(kThrowOnError))
387 .FromJust());
388 }
389 }
390 if (mode == PropertiesEnumerationMode::kEnumerationOrder) {
391 if (process_symbol_only || !has_symbol) {
392 return Just(true);
393 }
394 if (has_symbol) {
395 process_symbol_only = true;
396 }
397 } else {
398 DCHECK_EQ(mode, PropertiesEnumerationMode::kPropertyAdditionOrder);
399 return Just(true);
400 }
401 }
402 UNREACHABLE();
403}
404} // namespace

406// static
407Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::SetOrCopyDataProperties(
408 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target,
409 DirectHandle<Object> source, PropertiesEnumerationMode mode,
410 base::Vector<DirectHandle<Object>> excluded_properties, bool use_set) {
411 Maybe<bool> fast_assign =
412 FastAssign(isolate, target, source, mode, excluded_properties, use_set);
413 if (fast_assign.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
414 if (fast_assign.FromJust()) return Just(true);
415
416 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> from =
417 Object::ToObject(isolate, source).ToHandleChecked();
418
419 // 3b. Let keys be ? from.[[OwnPropertyKeys]]().
420 DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
421 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
422 isolate, keys,
423 KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, from, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
424 ALL_PROPERTIES, GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers),
425 Nothing<bool>());
426
427 if (!from->HasFastProperties() && target->HasFastProperties() &&
428 IsJSObject(*target) && !IsJSGlobalProxy(*target)) {
429 // Convert to slow properties if we're guaranteed to overflow the number of
430 // descriptors.
431 int source_length;
432 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*from)) {
433 source_length = Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*from)
434 ->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad)
435 ->NumberOfEnumerableProperties();
436 } else if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
437 source_length =
438 from->property_dictionary_swiss()->NumberOfEnumerableProperties();
439 } else {
440 source_length =
441 from->property_dictionary()->NumberOfEnumerableProperties();
442 }
443 if (source_length > kMaxNumberOfDescriptors) {
444 JSObject::NormalizeProperties(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(target),
445 CLEAR_INOBJECT_PROPERTIES, source_length,
446 "Copying data properties");
447 }
448 }
449
450 // 4. Repeat for each element nextKey of keys in List order,
451 for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
452 DirectHandle<Object> next_key(keys->get(i), isolate);
453 if (!excluded_properties.empty() &&
454 HasExcludedProperty(excluded_properties, next_key)) {
455 continue;
456 }
457
458 // 4a i. Let desc be ? from.[[GetOwnProperty]](nextKey).
459 PropertyDescriptor desc;
460 Maybe<bool> found =
461 JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, from, next_key, &desc);
462 if (found.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
463 // 4a ii. If desc is not undefined and desc.[[Enumerable]] is true, then
464 if (found.FromJust() && desc.enumerable()) {
465 // 4a ii 1. Let propValue be ? Get(from, nextKey).
466 DirectHandle<Object> prop_value;
467 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
468 isolate, prop_value,
469 Runtime::GetObjectProperty(isolate, from, next_key), Nothing<bool>());
470
471 if (use_set) {
472 // 4c ii 2. Let status be ? Set(to, nextKey, propValue, true).
473 DirectHandle<Object> status;
474 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
475 isolate, status,
476 Runtime::SetObjectProperty(isolate, target, next_key, prop_value,
477 StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
478 Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError)),
479 Nothing<bool>());
480 } else {
481 // 4a ii 2. Perform ! CreateDataProperty(target, nextKey, propValue).
482 PropertyKey key(isolate, next_key);
483 CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, target, key, prop_value,
484 Just(kThrowOnError))
485 .FromJust());
486 }
487 }
488 }
489
490 return Just(true);
491}
492
493Tagged<String> JSReceiver::class_name() {
494 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
495 if (IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(*this)) {
496 return roots.Function_string();
497 }
498 if (IsJSArgumentsObject(*this)) return roots.Arguments_string();
499 if (IsJSArray(*this)) return roots.Array_string();
500 if (IsJSArrayBuffer(*this)) {
501 if (Cast<JSArrayBuffer>(*this)->is_shared()) {
502 return roots.SharedArrayBuffer_string();
503 }
504 return roots.ArrayBuffer_string();
505 }
506 if (IsJSArrayIterator(*this)) return roots.ArrayIterator_string();
507 if (IsJSDate(*this)) return roots.Date_string();
508 if (IsJSError(*this)) return roots.Error_string();
509 if (IsJSGeneratorObject(*this)) return roots.Generator_string();
510 if (IsJSMap(*this)) return roots.Map_string();
511 if (IsJSMapIterator(*this)) return roots.MapIterator_string();
512 if (IsJSProxy(*this)) {
513 return map()->is_callable() ? roots.Function_string()
514 : roots.Object_string();
515 }
516 if (IsJSRegExp(*this)) return roots.RegExp_string();
517 if (IsJSSet(*this)) return roots.Set_string();
518 if (IsJSSetIterator(*this)) return roots.SetIterator_string();
519 if (IsJSTypedArray(*this)) {
520#define SWITCH_KIND(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
521 if (map()->elements_kind() == TYPE##_ELEMENTS) { \
522 return roots.Type##Array_string(); \
523 }
524 TYPED_ARRAYS(SWITCH_KIND)
525#undef SWITCH_KIND
526 }
527 if (IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*this)) {
528 Tagged<Object> value = Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(*this)->value();
529 if (IsBoolean(value)) return roots.Boolean_string();
530 if (IsString(value)) return roots.String_string();
531 if (IsNumber(value)) return roots.Number_string();
532 if (IsBigInt(value)) return roots.BigInt_string();
533 if (IsSymbol(value)) return roots.Symbol_string();
534 if (IsScript(value)) return roots.Script_string();
535 UNREACHABLE();
536 }
537 if (IsJSWeakMap(*this)) return roots.WeakMap_string();
538 if (IsJSWeakSet(*this)) return roots.WeakSet_string();
539 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*this)) return roots.global_string();
540 if (IsShared(*this)) {
541 if (IsJSSharedStruct(*this)) return roots.SharedStruct_string();
542 if (IsJSSharedArray(*this)) return roots.SharedArray_string();
543 if (IsJSAtomicsMutex(*this)) return roots.AtomicsMutex_string();
544 if (IsJSAtomicsCondition(*this)) return roots.AtomicsCondition_string();
545 // Other shared values are primitives.
546 UNREACHABLE();
547 }
548
549 return roots.Object_string();
550}
551
552namespace {
553std::pair<MaybeHandle<JSFunction>, Handle<String>> GetConstructorHelper(
554 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
555 // If the object was instantiated simply with base == new.target, the
556 // constructor on the map provides the most accurate name.
557 // Don't provide the info for prototypes, since their constructors are
558 // reclaimed and replaced by Object in OptimizeAsPrototype.
559 if (!IsJSProxy(*receiver) && receiver->map()->new_target_is_base() &&
560 !receiver->map()->is_prototype_map()) {
561 DirectHandle<Object> maybe_constructor(receiver->map()->GetConstructor(),
562 isolate);
563 if (IsJSFunction(*maybe_constructor)) {
564 DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor =
565 Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
566 Handle<String> name = SharedFunctionInfo::DebugName(
567 isolate, direct_handle(constructor->shared(), isolate));
568 if (name->length() != 0 &&
569 !name->Equals(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).Object_string())) {
570 return std::make_pair(indirect_handle(constructor, isolate), name);
571 }
572 } else if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*maybe_constructor)) {
573 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template =
574 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(maybe_constructor);
575 if (!IsUndefined(function_template->class_name(), isolate)) {
576 return std::make_pair(
577 MaybeHandle<JSFunction>(),
578 handle(Cast<String>(function_template->class_name()), isolate));
579 }
580 }
581 }
582
583 for (PrototypeIterator it(isolate, receiver, kStartAtReceiver); !it.IsAtEnd();
584 it.AdvanceIgnoringProxies()) {
585 auto current = PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<JSReceiver>(it);
586
587 LookupIterator it_to_string_tag(
588 isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->to_string_tag_symbol(), current,
589 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
590 auto maybe_to_string_tag = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
591 &it_to_string_tag, AllocationPolicy::kAllocationDisallowed);
592 if (IsString(*maybe_to_string_tag)) {
593 return std::make_pair(MaybeHandle<JSFunction>(),
594 Cast<String>(maybe_to_string_tag));
595 }
596
597 // Consider the following example:
598 //
599 // function A() {}
600 // function B() {}
601 // B.prototype = new A();
602 // B.prototype.constructor = B;
603 //
604 // The constructor name for `B.prototype` must yield "A", so we don't take
605 // "constructor" into account for the receiver itself, but only starting
606 // on the prototype chain.
607 if (!receiver.is_identical_to(current)) {
608 LookupIterator it_constructor(
609 isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->constructor_string(), current,
610 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
611 auto maybe_constructor = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
612 &it_constructor, AllocationPolicy::kAllocationDisallowed);
613 if (IsJSFunction(*maybe_constructor)) {
614 auto constructor = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
615 auto name = SharedFunctionInfo::DebugName(
616 isolate, direct_handle(constructor->shared(), isolate));
617
618 if (name->length() != 0 &&
619 !name->Equals(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).Object_string())) {
620 return std::make_pair(constructor, name);
621 }
622 }
623 }
624 }
625
626 return std::make_pair(MaybeHandle<JSFunction>(),
627 handle(receiver->class_name(), isolate));
628}
629} // anonymous namespace
630
631// static
632MaybeHandle<JSFunction> JSReceiver::GetConstructor(
633 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
634 return GetConstructorHelper(isolate, receiver).first;
635}
636
637// static
638Handle<String> JSReceiver::GetConstructorName(
639 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
640 return GetConstructorHelper(isolate, receiver).second;
641}
642
643// static
644MaybeHandle<NativeContext> JSReceiver::GetFunctionRealm(
645 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
646 Isolate* isolate = receiver->GetIsolate();
647 // This is implemented as a loop because it's possible to construct very
648 // long chains of bound functions or proxies where a recursive implementation
649 // would run out of stack space.
650 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
651 Tagged<JSReceiver> current = *receiver;
652 do {
653 DCHECK(current->map()->is_constructor());
654 InstanceType instance_type = current->map()->instance_type();
655 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSProxy(instance_type)) {
656 Tagged<JSProxy> proxy = Cast<JSProxy>(current);
657 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
658 AllowGarbageCollection allow_allocating_errors;
659 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked));
660 }
661 current = Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target());
662 continue;
663 }
664 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(instance_type)) {
665 Tagged<JSFunction> function = Cast<JSFunction>(current);
666 return handle(function->native_context(), isolate);
667 }
668 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSBoundFunction(instance_type)) {
669 Tagged<JSBoundFunction> function = Cast<JSBoundFunction>(current);
670 current = function->bound_target_function();
671 continue;
672 }
673 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSWrappedFunction(instance_type)) {
674 Tagged<JSWrappedFunction> function = Cast<JSWrappedFunction>(current);
675 current = function->wrapped_target_function();
676 continue;
677 }
678 Tagged<JSObject> object = Cast<JSObject>(current);
679 DCHECK(!IsJSFunction(object));
680 return object->GetCreationContext(isolate);
681 } while (true);
682}
683
684// static
685MaybeHandle<NativeContext> JSReceiver::GetContextForMicrotask(
686 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
687 Isolate* isolate = receiver->GetIsolate();
688 while (IsJSBoundFunction(*receiver) || IsJSProxy(*receiver)) {
689 if (IsJSBoundFunction(*receiver)) {
690 receiver = direct_handle(
691 Cast<JSBoundFunction>(receiver)->bound_target_function(), isolate);
692 } else {
693 DCHECK(IsJSProxy(*receiver));
694 DirectHandle<Object> target(Cast<JSProxy>(receiver)->target(), isolate);
695 if (!IsJSReceiver(*target)) return MaybeHandle<NativeContext>();
696 receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(target);
697 }
698 }
699
700 if (!IsJSFunction(*receiver)) return MaybeHandle<NativeContext>();
701 return handle(Cast<JSFunction>(receiver)->native_context(), isolate);
702}
703
704Maybe<PropertyAttributes> JSReceiver::GetPropertyAttributes(
705 LookupIterator* it) {
706 for (;; it->Next()) {
707 switch (it->state()) {
708 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
709 UNREACHABLE();
710 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
711 return JSProxy::GetPropertyAttributes(it);
712 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
713 return Just(ABSENT);
714 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
715 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> result =
716 JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptor(it);
717 if (result.IsNothing()) return result;
718 if (result.FromJust() != ABSENT) return result;
719 continue;
720 }
721 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
722 if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
723 return JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithFailedAccessCheck(it);
724 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
725 return Just(ABSENT);
726 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
727 if (IsJSModuleNamespace(*it->GetHolder<Object>())) {
728 return JSModuleNamespace::GetPropertyAttributes(it);
729 } else {
730 return Just(it->property_attributes());
731 }
732 case LookupIterator::DATA:
733 return Just(it->property_attributes());
734 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
735 return Just(ABSENT);
736 }
737 UNREACHABLE();
738 }
739}
740
741namespace {
742
743Tagged<Object> SetHashAndUpdateProperties(Tagged<HeapObject> properties,
744 int hash) {
745 DCHECK_NE(PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel, hash);
746 DCHECK(PropertyArray::HashField::is_valid(hash));
747
748 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
749 if (properties == roots.empty_fixed_array() ||
750 properties == roots.empty_property_array() ||
751 properties == roots.empty_property_dictionary() ||
752 properties == roots.empty_swiss_property_dictionary()) {
753 return Smi::FromInt(hash);
754 }
755
756 if (IsPropertyArray(properties)) {
757 Cast<PropertyArray>(properties)->SetHash(hash);
758 DCHECK_LT(0, Cast<PropertyArray>(properties)->length());
759 return properties;
760 }
761
762 if (IsGlobalDictionary(properties)) {
763 Cast<GlobalDictionary>(properties)->SetHash(hash);
764 return properties;
765 }
766
767 DCHECK(IsPropertyDictionary(properties));
768 Cast<PropertyDictionary>(properties)->SetHash(hash);
769
770 return properties;
771}
772
773int GetIdentityHashHelper(Tagged<JSReceiver> object) {
774 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
775 Tagged<Object> properties = object->raw_properties_or_hash();
776 if (IsSmi(properties)) {
777 return Smi::ToInt(properties);
778 }
779
780 if (IsPropertyArray(properties)) {
781 return Cast<PropertyArray>(properties)->Hash();
782 }
783
784 if (IsPropertyDictionary(properties)) {
785 return Cast<PropertyDictionary>(properties)->Hash();
786 }
787
788 if (IsGlobalDictionary(properties)) {
789 return Cast<GlobalDictionary>(properties)->Hash();
790 }
791
792#ifdef DEBUG
793 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
794 DCHECK(properties == roots.empty_fixed_array() ||
795 properties == roots.empty_property_dictionary() ||
796 properties == roots.empty_swiss_property_dictionary());
797#endif
798
799 return PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel;
800}
801} // namespace
802
803void JSReceiver::SetIdentityHash(int hash) {
804 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
805 DCHECK_NE(PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel, hash);
806 DCHECK(PropertyArray::HashField::is_valid(hash));
807
808 Tagged<HeapObject> existing_properties =
809 Cast<HeapObject>(raw_properties_or_hash());
810 Tagged<Object> new_properties =
811 SetHashAndUpdateProperties(existing_properties, hash);
812 set_raw_properties_or_hash(new_properties, kRelaxedStore);
813}
814
815void JSReceiver::SetProperties(Tagged<HeapObject> properties) {
816 DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsPropertyArray(properties) &&
817 Cast<PropertyArray>(properties)->length() == 0,
818 properties == GetReadOnlyRoots().empty_property_array());
819 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
820 int hash = GetIdentityHashHelper(*this);
821 Tagged<Object> new_properties = properties;
822
823 // TODO(cbruni): Make GetIdentityHashHelper return a bool so that we
824 // don't have to manually compare against kNoHashSentinel.
825 if (hash != PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel) {
826 new_properties = SetHashAndUpdateProperties(properties, hash);
827 }
828
829 set_raw_properties_or_hash(new_properties, kRelaxedStore);
830}
831
832Tagged<Object> JSReceiver::GetIdentityHash() {
833 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
834
835 int hash = GetIdentityHashHelper(*this);
836 if (hash == PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel) {
837 return GetReadOnlyRoots().undefined_value();
838 }
839
840 return Smi::FromInt(hash);
841}
842
843// static
844Tagged<Smi> JSReceiver::CreateIdentityHash(Isolate* isolate,
845 Tagged<JSReceiver> key) {
846 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
847 int hash = isolate->GenerateIdentityHash(PropertyArray::HashField::kMax);
848 DCHECK_NE(PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel, hash);
849
850 key->SetIdentityHash(hash);
851 return Smi::FromInt(hash);
852}
853
854Tagged<Smi> JSReceiver::GetOrCreateIdentityHash(Isolate* isolate) {
855 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
856
857 int hash = GetIdentityHashHelper(*this);
858 if (hash != PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel) {
859 return Smi::FromInt(hash);
860 }
861
862 return JSReceiver::CreateIdentityHash(isolate, *this);
863}
864
865void JSReceiver::DeleteNormalizedProperty(DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
866 InternalIndex entry) {
867 DCHECK(!object->HasFastProperties());
868 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
869 DCHECK(entry.is_found());
870
871 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*object)) {
872 // If we have a global object, invalidate the cell and remove it from the
873 // global object's dictionary.
874 DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary(
875 Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*object)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad),
876 isolate);
877
878 DirectHandle<PropertyCell> cell(dictionary->CellAt(entry), isolate);
879
880 DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> new_dictionary =
881 GlobalDictionary::DeleteEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry);
882 Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*object)->set_global_dictionary(*new_dictionary,
883 kReleaseStore);
884
885 cell->ClearAndInvalidate(isolate);
886 } else {
887 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
888 DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> dictionary(
889 object->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate);
890
891 dictionary = SwissNameDictionary::DeleteEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry);
892 object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
893 } else {
894 DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary(object->property_dictionary(),
895 isolate);
896
897 dictionary = NameDictionary::DeleteEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry);
898 object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
899 }
900 }
901 if (object->map()->is_prototype_map()) {
902 // Invalidate prototype validity cell as this may invalidate transitioning
903 // store IC handlers.
904 JSObject::InvalidatePrototypeChains(object->map());
905 }
906}
907
908Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::DeleteProperty(LookupIterator* it,
909 LanguageMode language_mode) {
910 it->UpdateProtector();
911
912 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
913
914 if (it->state() == LookupIterator::JSPROXY) {
915 return JSProxy::DeletePropertyOrElement(it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
916 it->GetName(), language_mode);
917 }
918
919 if (IsJSProxy(*it->GetReceiver())) {
920 if (it->state() != LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND) {
921 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::DATA, it->state());
922 DCHECK(it->name()->IsPrivate());
923 it->Delete();
924 }
925 return Just(true);
926 }
927
928 for (;; it->Next()) {
929 switch (it->state()) {
930 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
931 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
932 UNREACHABLE();
933 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
934 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
935 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
936 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
937 if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
938 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
939 isolate,
940 isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it->GetHolder<JSObject>()),
941 Nothing<bool>());
942 UNREACHABLE();
943 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
944 ShouldThrow should_throw =
945 is_sloppy(language_mode) ? kDontThrow : kThrowOnError;
946 InterceptorResult result;
947 if (!JSObject::DeletePropertyWithInterceptor(it, should_throw)
948 .To(&result)) {
949 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
950 return Nothing<bool>();
951 }
952 switch (result) {
953 case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
954 return Just(false);
955 case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
956 return Just(true);
957 case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
958 // Proceed lookup.
959 continue;
960 }
961 UNREACHABLE();
962 }
963 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
964 return Just(true);
965 case LookupIterator::DATA:
966 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
967 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
968 if (!it->IsConfigurable() ||
969 (IsJSTypedArray(*holder) && it->IsElement(*holder))) {
970 // Fail if the property is not configurable if the property is a
971 // TypedArray element.
972 if (is_strict(language_mode)) {
973 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
974 MessageTemplate::kStrictDeleteProperty, it->GetName(),
975 it->GetReceiver()));
976 return Nothing<bool>();
977 }
978 return Just(false);
979 }
980
981 it->Delete();
982
983 return Just(true);
984 }
985 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
986 return Just(true);
987 }
988 UNREACHABLE();
989 }
990}
991
992Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::DeleteElement(Isolate* isolate,
993 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
994 uint32_t index,
995 LanguageMode language_mode) {
996 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, index, object, LookupIterator::OWN);
997 return DeleteProperty(&it, language_mode);
998}
999
1000Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::DeleteProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1001 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
1002 DirectHandle<Name> name,
1003 LanguageMode language_mode) {
1004 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, name, object, LookupIterator::OWN);
1005 return DeleteProperty(&it, language_mode);
1006}
1007
1008Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::DeletePropertyOrElement(Isolate* isolate,
1009 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
1010 DirectHandle<Name> name,
1011 LanguageMode language_mode) {
1012 PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
1013 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, object, LookupIterator::OWN);
1014 return DeleteProperty(&it, language_mode);
1015}
1016
1017// ES6 19.1.2.4
1018// static
1019Tagged<Object> JSReceiver::DefineProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1020 DirectHandle<Object> object,
1021 DirectHandle<Object> key,
1022 Handle<Object> attributes) {
1023 // 1. If Type(O) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
1024 if (!IsJSReceiver(*object)) {
1025 DirectHandle<String> fun_name =
1026 isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String("Object.defineProperty");
1027 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_FAILURE(
1028 isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject, fun_name));
1029 }
1030 // 2. Let key be ToPropertyKey(P).
1031 // 3. ReturnIfAbrupt(key).
1032 ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, key,
1033 Object::ToPropertyKey(isolate, key));
1034 // 4. Let desc be ToPropertyDescriptor(Attributes).
1035 // 5. ReturnIfAbrupt(desc).
1036 PropertyDescriptor desc;
1037 if (!PropertyDescriptor::ToPropertyDescriptor(
1038 isolate, Cast<JSAny>(attributes), &desc)) {
1039 return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).exception();
1040 }
1041 // 6. Let success be DefinePropertyOrThrow(O,key, desc).
1042 Maybe<bool> success = DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(object),
1043 key, &desc, Just(kThrowOnError));
1044 // 7. ReturnIfAbrupt(success).
1045 MAYBE_RETURN(success, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).exception());
1046 CHECK(success.FromJust());
1047 // 8. Return O.
1048 return *object;
1049}
1050
1051// ES6 19.1.2.3.1
1052// static
1053MaybeHandle<Object> JSReceiver::DefineProperties(
1054 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> object, DirectHandle<Object> properties) {
1055 // 1. If Type(O) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
1056 if (!IsJSReceiver(*object)) {
1057 DirectHandle<String> fun_name =
1058 isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String("Object.defineProperties");
1059 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1060 isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject, fun_name));
1061 }
1062 // 2. Let props be ToObject(Properties).
1063 // 3. ReturnIfAbrupt(props).
1064 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> props;
1065 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, props,
1066 Object::ToObject(isolate, properties));
1067
1068 // 4. Let keys be props.[[OwnPropertyKeys]]().
1069 // 5. ReturnIfAbrupt(keys).
1070 DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
1071 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1072 isolate, keys,
1073 KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, props, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
1074 ALL_PROPERTIES));
1075 // 6. Let descriptors be an empty List.s
1076 int capacity = keys->length();
1077 std::vector<PropertyDescriptor> descriptors(capacity);
1078 size_t descriptors_index = 0;
1079 // 7. Repeat for each element nextKey of keys in List order,
1080 for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
1081 DirectHandle<JSAny> next_key(Cast<JSAny>(keys->get(i)), isolate);
1082 // 7a. Let propDesc be props.[[GetOwnProperty]](nextKey).
1083 // 7b. ReturnIfAbrupt(propDesc).
1084 PropertyKey key(isolate, next_key);
1085 LookupIterator it(isolate, props, key, LookupIterator::OWN);
1086 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> maybe = JSReceiver::GetPropertyAttributes(&it);
1087 if (maybe.IsNothing()) return MaybeHandle<Object>();
1088 PropertyAttributes attrs = maybe.FromJust();
1089 // 7c. If propDesc is not undefined and propDesc.[[Enumerable]] is true:
1090 if (attrs == ABSENT) continue;
1091 if (attrs & DONT_ENUM) continue;
1092 // 7c i. Let descObj be Get(props, nextKey).
1093 // 7c ii. ReturnIfAbrupt(descObj).
1094 Handle<JSAny> desc_obj;
1095 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, desc_obj,
1096 Cast<JSAny>(Object::GetProperty(&it)));
1097 // 7c iii. Let desc be ToPropertyDescriptor(descObj).
1098 bool success = PropertyDescriptor::ToPropertyDescriptor(
1099 isolate, desc_obj, &descriptors[descriptors_index]);
1100 // 7c iv. ReturnIfAbrupt(desc).
1101 if (!success) return MaybeHandle<Object>();
1102 // 7c v. Append the pair (a two element List) consisting of nextKey and
1103 // desc to the end of descriptors.
1104 descriptors[descriptors_index].set_name(next_key);
1105 descriptors_index++;
1106 }
1107 // 8. For each pair from descriptors in list order,
1108 for (size_t i = 0; i < descriptors_index; ++i) {
1109 PropertyDescriptor* desc = &descriptors[i];
1110 // 8a. Let P be the first element of pair.
1111 // 8b. Let desc be the second element of pair.
1112 // 8c. Let status be DefinePropertyOrThrow(O, P, desc).
1113 Maybe<bool> status =
1114 DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(object), desc->name(), desc,
1115 Just(kThrowOnError));
1116 // 8d. ReturnIfAbrupt(status).
1117 if (status.IsNothing()) return MaybeHandle<Object>();
1118 CHECK(status.FromJust());
1119 }
1120 // 9. Return o.
1121 return object;
1122}
1123
1124// static
1125Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1126 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
1127 DirectHandle<Object> key,
1128 PropertyDescriptor* desc,
1129 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1130 if (IsJSArray(*object)) {
1131 return JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSArray>(object), key, desc,
1132 should_throw);
1133 }
1134 if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
1135 return JSProxy::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSProxy>(object), key, desc,
1136 should_throw);
1137 }
1138 if (IsJSTypedArray(*object)) {
1139 return JSTypedArray::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSTypedArray>(object),
1140 key, desc, should_throw);
1141 }
1142 if (IsJSModuleNamespace(*object)) {
1143 return JSModuleNamespace::DefineOwnProperty(
1144 isolate, Cast<JSModuleNamespace>(object), key, desc, should_throw);
1145 }
1146 if (IsWasmObject(*object)) {
1147 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
1148 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
1149 }
1150 if (IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*object)) {
1151 return AlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject::DefineOwnProperty(
1152 isolate, Cast<AlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject>(object), key, desc,
1153 should_throw);
1154 }
1155
1156 // OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty, by virtue of calling
1157 // DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes, can handle arguments
1158 // (ES#sec-arguments-exotic-objects-defineownproperty-p-desc).
1159 return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object), key, desc,
1160 should_throw);
1161}
1162
1163// static
1164Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(
1165 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<Object> key,
1166 PropertyDescriptor* desc, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1167 DCHECK(IsName(*key) || IsNumber(*key)); // |key| is a PropertyKey.
1168 PropertyKey lookup_key(isolate, key);
1169 return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, object, lookup_key, desc,
1170 should_throw);
1171}
1172
1173namespace {
1174
1175MaybeHandle<JSAny> GetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(
1176 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor, bool* done) {
1177 *done = false;
1178 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1179 // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
1180 // interceptor calls.
1181 AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
1182
1183 if (IsUndefined(interceptor->getter(), isolate)) {
1184 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1185 }
1186
1187 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1188 DirectHandle<JSAny> result;
1189 DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1190 if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1191 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, receiver,
1192 Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver));
1193 }
1194 PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1195 *holder, Just(kDontThrow));
1196
1197 if (it->IsElement(*holder)) {
1198 result = args.CallIndexedGetter(interceptor, it->array_index());
1199 } else {
1200 result = args.CallNamedGetter(interceptor, it->name());
1201 }
1202 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1203 RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, args, kNullMaybeHandle);
1204 if (result.is_null()) return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1205 *done = true;
1206 args.AcceptSideEffects();
1207 // Rebox handle before return
1208 return handle(*result, isolate);
1209}
1210
1211Maybe<PropertyAttributes> GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptorInternal(
1212 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor) {
1213 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1214 // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing
1215 // callbacks or interceptor calls.
1216 AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
1217 HandleScope scope(isolate);
1218
1219 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1220 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!it->IsElement(*holder) && IsSymbol(*it->name()),
1221 interceptor->can_intercept_symbols());
1222 DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1223 if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1224 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
1225 Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1226 Nothing<PropertyAttributes>());
1227 }
1228 PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1229 *holder, Just(kDontThrow));
1230 if (!IsUndefined(interceptor->query(), isolate)) {
1231 DirectHandle<Object> result;
1232 if (it->IsElement(*holder)) {
1233 result = args.CallIndexedQuery(interceptor, it->array_index());
1234 } else {
1235 result = args.CallNamedQuery(interceptor, it->name());
1236 }
1237 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1238 RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, args,
1239 Nothing<PropertyAttributes>());
1240
1241 if (!result.is_null()) {
1242 int32_t value;
1243 CHECK(Object::ToInt32(*result, &value));
1244 DCHECK_IMPLIES((value & ~PropertyAttributes::ALL_ATTRIBUTES_MASK) != 0,
1245 value == PropertyAttributes::ABSENT);
1246 // In case of absent property side effects are not allowed.
1247 // TODO(ishell): PropertyAttributes::ABSENT is not exposed in the Api,
1248 // so it can't be officially returned. We should fix the tests instead.
1249 if (value != PropertyAttributes::ABSENT) {
1250 args.AcceptSideEffects();
1251 }
1252 return Just(static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(value));
1253 }
1254 } else if (!IsUndefined(interceptor->getter(), isolate)) {
1255 // TODO(verwaest): Use GetPropertyWithInterceptor?
1256 DirectHandle<Object> result;
1257 if (it->IsElement(*holder)) {
1258 result = args.CallIndexedGetter(interceptor, it->array_index());
1259 } else {
1260 result = args.CallNamedGetter(interceptor, it->name());
1261 }
1262 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1263 RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, args,
1264 Nothing<PropertyAttributes>());
1265
1266 if (!result.is_null()) {
1267 args.AcceptSideEffects();
1268 return Just(DONT_ENUM);
1269 }
1270 }
1271 return Just(ABSENT);
1272}
1273
1274Maybe<InterceptorResult> SetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(
1275 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor,
1276 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw, DirectHandle<Object> value) {
1277 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1278 // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
1279 // interceptor calls.
1280 AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
1281
1282 if (IsUndefined(interceptor->setter(), isolate)) {
1283 return Just(InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted);
1284 }
1285
1286 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1287 DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1288 if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1289 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
1290 Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1291 Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
1292 }
1293 PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1294 *holder, should_throw);
1295
1296 v8::Intercepted intercepted =
1297 it->IsElement(*holder)
1298 ? args.CallIndexedSetter(interceptor, it->array_index(), value)
1299 : args.CallNamedSetter(interceptor, it->name(), value);
1300
1301 return args.GetBooleanReturnValue(intercepted, "Setter");
1302}
1303
1304Maybe<InterceptorResult> DefinePropertyWithInterceptorInternal(
1305 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor,
1306 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw, PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
1307 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1308 // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
1309 // interceptor calls.
1310 AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
1311
1312 if (IsUndefined(interceptor->definer(), isolate)) {
1313 return Just(InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted);
1314 }
1315
1316 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1317 DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1318 if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1319 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
1320 Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1321 Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
1322 }
1323
1324 std::unique_ptr<v8::PropertyDescriptor> descriptor(
1325 new v8::PropertyDescriptor());
1326 if (PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(desc)) {
1327 DirectHandle<Object> getter = desc->get();
1328 if (!getter.is_null() && IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter)) {
1329 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1330 isolate, getter,
1331 ApiNatives::InstantiateFunction(isolate,
1332 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(getter),
1333 MaybeDirectHandle<Name>()),
1334 Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
1335 }
1336 DirectHandle<Object> setter = desc->set();
1337 if (!setter.is_null() && IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter)) {
1338 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1339 isolate, setter,
1340 ApiNatives::InstantiateFunction(isolate,
1341 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(setter),
1342 MaybeDirectHandle<Name>()),
1343 Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
1344 }
1345 descriptor.reset(new v8::PropertyDescriptor(v8::Utils::ToLocal(getter),
1346 v8::Utils::ToLocal(setter)));
1347 } else if (PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(desc)) {
1348 if (desc->has_writable()) {
1349 descriptor.reset(new v8::PropertyDescriptor(
1350 v8::Utils::ToLocal(desc->value()), desc->writable()));
1351 } else {
1352 descriptor.reset(
1353 new v8::PropertyDescriptor(v8::Utils::ToLocal(desc->value())));
1354 }
1355 }
1356 if (desc->has_enumerable()) {
1357 descriptor->set_enumerable(desc->enumerable());
1358 }
1359 if (desc->has_configurable()) {
1360 descriptor->set_configurable(desc->configurable());
1361 }
1362
1363 PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1364 *holder, should_throw);
1365
1366 v8::Intercepted intercepted =
1367 it->IsElement(*holder)
1368 ? args.CallIndexedDefiner(interceptor, it->array_index(), *descriptor)
1369 : args.CallNamedDefiner(interceptor, it->name(), *descriptor);
1370
1371 return args.GetBooleanReturnValue(intercepted, "Definer");
1372}
1373
1374} // namespace
1375
1376// ES6 9.1.6.1
1377// static
1378Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(
1379 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, const PropertyKey& key,
1380 PropertyDescriptor* desc, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1381 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN);
1382
1383 // Deal with access checks first.
1384 while (it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
1385 if (!it.HasAccess()) {
1386 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1387 isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it.GetHolder<JSObject>()),
1388 Nothing<bool>());
1389 UNREACHABLE();
1390 }
1391 it.Next();
1392 }
1393
1394 // 1. Let current be O.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
1395 // 2. ReturnIfAbrupt(current).
1396 PropertyDescriptor current;
1397 MAYBE_RETURN(GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(&it, &current), Nothing<bool>());
1398
1399 // TODO(jkummerow/verwaest): It would be nice if we didn't have to reset
1400 // the iterator every time. Currently, the reasons why we need it are because
1401 // GetOwnPropertyDescriptor can have side effects, namely:
1402 // - Interceptors
1403 // - Accessors (which might change the holder's map)
1404 it.Restart();
1405
1406 // Skip over the access check after restarting -- we've already checked it.
1407 while (it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
1408 DCHECK(it.HasAccess());
1409 it.Next();
1410 }
1411
1412 // Handle interceptor.
1413 if (it.state() == LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR) {
1414 if (it.HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
1415 InterceptorResult result;
1416 if (!DefinePropertyWithInterceptorInternal(&it, it.GetInterceptor(),
1417 should_throw, desc)
1418 .To(&result)) {
1419 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1420 return Nothing<bool>();
1421 }
1422 switch (result) {
1423 case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
1424 return Just(false);
1425 case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
1426 return Just(true);
1427
1428 case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
1429 // Proceed lookup.
1430 break;
1431 }
1432 // We need to restart the lookup in case the interceptor ran with side
1433 // effects.
1434 it.Restart();
1435 }
1436 }
1437
1438 // 3. Let extensible be the value of the [[Extensible]] internal slot of O.
1439 bool extensible = JSObject::IsExtensible(isolate, object);
1440
1441 return ValidateAndApplyPropertyDescriptor(isolate, &it, extensible, desc,
1442 &current, should_throw, {});
1443}
1444
1445// ES6 9.1.6.2
1446// static
1447Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor(
1448 Isolate* isolate, bool extensible, PropertyDescriptor* desc,
1449 PropertyDescriptor* current, DirectHandle<Name> property_name,
1450 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1451 // 1. Return ValidateAndApplyPropertyDescriptor(undefined, undefined,
1452 // Extensible, Desc, Current).
1453 return ValidateAndApplyPropertyDescriptor(
1454 isolate, nullptr, extensible, desc, current, should_throw, property_name);
1455}
1456
1457// https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-validateandapplypropertydescriptor
1458// static
1459Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::ValidateAndApplyPropertyDescriptor(
1460 Isolate* isolate, LookupIterator* it, bool extensible,
1461 PropertyDescriptor* desc, PropertyDescriptor* current,
1462 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw, DirectHandle<Name> property_name) {
1463 // We either need a LookupIterator, or a property name.
1464 DCHECK((it == nullptr) != property_name.is_null());
1465 bool desc_is_data_descriptor = PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(desc);
1466 bool desc_is_accessor_descriptor =
1467 PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(desc);
1468 bool desc_is_generic_descriptor =
1469 PropertyDescriptor::IsGenericDescriptor(desc);
1470 // 1. (Assert)
1471 // 2. If current is undefined, then
1472 if (current->is_empty()) {
1473 // 2a. If extensible is false, return false.
1474 if (!extensible) {
1475 RETURN_FAILURE(
1476 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1477 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed,
1478 it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1479 }
1480 // 2c. If IsGenericDescriptor(Desc) or IsDataDescriptor(Desc) is true, then:
1481 // (This is equivalent to !IsAccessorDescriptor(desc).)
1482 DCHECK_EQ(desc_is_generic_descriptor || desc_is_data_descriptor,
1483 !desc_is_accessor_descriptor);
1484 if (!desc_is_accessor_descriptor) {
1485 // 2c i. If O is not undefined, create an own data property named P of
1486 // object O whose [[Value]], [[Writable]], [[Enumerable]] and
1487 // [[Configurable]] attribute values are described by Desc. If the value
1488 // of an attribute field of Desc is absent, the attribute of the newly
1489 // created property is set to its default value.
1490 if (it != nullptr) {
1491 if (!desc->has_writable()) desc->set_writable(false);
1492 if (!desc->has_enumerable()) desc->set_enumerable(false);
1493 if (!desc->has_configurable()) desc->set_configurable(false);
1494 DirectHandle<Object> value(
1495 desc->has_value()
1496 ? desc->value()
1497 : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value()));
1498 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result =
1499 JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(it, value,
1500 desc->ToAttributes());
1501 if (result.is_null()) return Nothing<bool>();
1502 }
1503 } else {
1504 // 2d. Else Desc must be an accessor Property Descriptor,
1505 DCHECK(desc_is_accessor_descriptor);
1506 // 2d i. If O is not undefined, create an own accessor property named P
1507 // of object O whose [[Get]], [[Set]], [[Enumerable]] and
1508 // [[Configurable]] attribute values are described by Desc. If the value
1509 // of an attribute field of Desc is absent, the attribute of the newly
1510 // created property is set to its default value.
1511 if (it != nullptr) {
1512 if (!desc->has_enumerable()) desc->set_enumerable(false);
1513 if (!desc->has_configurable()) desc->set_configurable(false);
1514 DirectHandle<Object> getter(
1515 desc->has_get() ? desc->get()
1516 : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->null_value()));
1517 DirectHandle<Object> setter(
1518 desc->has_set() ? desc->set()
1519 : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->null_value()));
1520 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result =
1521 JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(it, getter, setter,
1522 desc->ToAttributes());
1523 if (result.is_null()) return Nothing<bool>();
1524 }
1525 }
1526 // 2e. Return true.
1527 return Just(true);
1528 }
1529 // 3. If every field in Desc is absent, return true. (This also has a shortcut
1530 // not in the spec: if every field value matches the current value, return.)
1531 if ((!desc->has_enumerable() ||
1532 desc->enumerable() == current->enumerable()) &&
1533 (!desc->has_configurable() ||
1534 desc->configurable() == current->configurable()) &&
1535 !desc->has_value() &&
1536 (!desc->has_writable() ||
1537 (current->has_writable() && current->writable() == desc->writable())) &&
1538 (!desc->has_get() ||
1539 (current->has_get() &&
1540 Object::SameValue(*current->get(), *desc->get()))) &&
1541 (!desc->has_set() ||
1542 (current->has_set() &&
1543 Object::SameValue(*current->set(), *desc->set())))) {
1544 return Just(true);
1545 }
1546 // 4. If current.[[Configurable]] is false, then
1547 if (!current->configurable()) {
1548 // 4a. If Desc.[[Configurable]] is present and its value is true, return
1549 // false.
1550 if (desc->has_configurable() && desc->configurable()) {
1551 RETURN_FAILURE(
1552 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1553 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1554 it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1555 }
1556 // 4b. If Desc.[[Enumerable]] is present and
1557 // ! SameValue(Desc.[[Enumerable]], current.[[Enumerable]]) is false, return
1558 // false.
1559 if (desc->has_enumerable() && desc->enumerable() != current->enumerable()) {
1560 RETURN_FAILURE(
1561 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1562 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1563 it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1564 }
1565 }
1566
1567 bool current_is_data_descriptor =
1568 PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(current);
1569 // 5. If ! IsGenericDescriptor(Desc) is true, no further validation is
1570 // required.
1571 if (desc_is_generic_descriptor) {
1572 // Nothing to see here.
1573
1574 // 6. Else if ! SameValue(!IsDataDescriptor(current),
1575 // !IsDataDescriptor(Desc)) is false, the
1576 } else if (current_is_data_descriptor != desc_is_data_descriptor) {
1577 // 6a. If current.[[Configurable]] is false, return false.
1578 if (!current->configurable()) {
1579 RETURN_FAILURE(
1580 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1581 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1582 it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1583 }
1584 // 6b. If IsDataDescriptor(current) is true, then:
1585 if (current_is_data_descriptor) {
1586 // 6b i. If O is not undefined, convert the property named P of object O
1587 // from a data property to an accessor property. Preserve the existing
1588 // values of the converted property's [[Configurable]] and [[Enumerable]]
1589 // attributes and set the rest of the property's attributes to their
1590 // default values.
1591 // --> Folded into step 9
1592 } else {
1593 // 6c i. If O is not undefined, convert the property named P of object O
1594 // from an accessor property to a data property. Preserve the existing
1595 // values of the converted propertyâ€™s [[Configurable]] and [[Enumerable]]
1596 // attributes and set the rest of the propertyâ€™s attributes to their
1597 // default values.
1598 // --> Folded into step 9
1599 }
1600
1601 // 7. Else if IsDataDescriptor(current) and IsDataDescriptor(Desc) are both
1602 // true, then:
1603 } else if (current_is_data_descriptor && desc_is_data_descriptor) {
1604 // 7a. If current.[[Configurable]] is false and current.[[Writable]] is
1605 // false, then
1606 if (!current->configurable() && !current->writable()) {
1607 // 7a i. If Desc.[[Writable]] is present and Desc.[[Writable]] is true,
1608 // return false.
1609 if (desc->has_writable() && desc->writable()) {
1610 RETURN_FAILURE(
1611 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1612 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1613 it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1614 }
1615 // 7a ii. If Desc.[[Value]] is present and SameValue(Desc.[[Value]],
1616 // current.[[Value]]) is false, return false.
1617 if (desc->has_value()) {
1618 // We'll succeed applying the property, but the value is already the
1619 // same and the property is read-only, so skip actually writing the
1620 // property. Otherwise we may try to e.g., write to frozen elements.
1621 if (Object::SameValue(*desc->value(), *current->value()))
1622 return Just(true);
1623 RETURN_FAILURE(
1624 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1625 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1626 it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1627 }
1628 }
1629 } else {
1630 // 8. Else,
1631 // 8a. Assert: ! IsAccessorDescriptor(current) and
1632 // ! IsAccessorDescriptor(Desc) are both true.
1633 DCHECK(PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(current) &&
1634 desc_is_accessor_descriptor);
1635 // 8b. If current.[[Configurable]] is false, then:
1636 if (!current->configurable()) {
1637 // 8a i. If Desc.[[Set]] is present and SameValue(Desc.[[Set]],
1638 // current.[[Set]]) is false, return false.
1639 if (desc->has_set() &&
1640 !Object::SameValue(*desc->set(), *current->set())) {
1641 RETURN_FAILURE(
1642 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1643 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1644 it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1645 }
1646 // 8a ii. If Desc.[[Get]] is present and SameValue(Desc.[[Get]],
1647 // current.[[Get]]) is false, return false.
1648 if (desc->has_get() &&
1649 !Object::SameValue(*desc->get(), *current->get())) {
1650 RETURN_FAILURE(
1651 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1652 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1653 it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1654 }
1655 }
1656 }
1657
1658 // 9. If O is not undefined, then:
1659 if (it != nullptr) {
1660 // 9a. For each field of Desc that is present, set the corresponding
1661 // attribute of the property named P of object O to the value of the field.
1662 PropertyAttributes attrs = NONE;
1663
1664 if (desc->has_enumerable()) {
1665 attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1666 attrs | (desc->enumerable() ? NONE : DONT_ENUM));
1667 } else {
1668 attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1669 attrs | (current->enumerable() ? NONE : DONT_ENUM));
1670 }
1671 if (desc->has_configurable()) {
1672 attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1673 attrs | (desc->configurable() ? NONE : DONT_DELETE));
1674 } else {
1675 attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1676 attrs | (current->configurable() ? NONE : DONT_DELETE));
1677 }
1678 if (desc_is_data_descriptor ||
1679 (desc_is_generic_descriptor && current_is_data_descriptor)) {
1680 if (desc->has_writable()) {
1681 attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1682 attrs | (desc->writable() ? NONE : READ_ONLY));
1683 } else {
1684 attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1685 attrs | (current->writable() ? NONE : READ_ONLY));
1686 }
1687 DirectHandle<Object> value(
1688 desc->has_value() ? desc->value()
1689 : current->has_value()
1690 ? current->value()
1691 : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value()));
1692 return JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(it, value, attrs,
1693 should_throw);
1694 } else {
1695 DCHECK(desc_is_accessor_descriptor ||
1696 (desc_is_generic_descriptor &&
1697 PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(current)));
1698 DirectHandle<Object> getter(
1699 desc->has_get() ? desc->get()
1700 : current->has_get()
1701 ? current->get()
1702 : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->null_value()));
1703 DirectHandle<Object> setter(
1704 desc->has_set() ? desc->set()
1705 : current->has_set()
1706 ? current->set()
1707 : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->null_value()));
1708 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result =
1709 JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(it, getter, setter,
1710 attrs);
1711 if (result.is_null()) return Nothing<bool>();
1712 }
1713 }
1714
1715 // 10. Return true.
1716 return Just(true);
1717}
1718
1719// static
1720Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1721 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
1722 DirectHandle<Name> key,
1723 DirectHandle<Object> value,
1724 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1725 return CreateDataProperty(isolate, object, PropertyKey(isolate, key), value,
1726 should_throw);
1727}
1728
1729// static
1730Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1731 DirectHandle<JSAny> object,
1732 PropertyKey key,
1733 DirectHandle<Object> value,
1734 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1735 if (!IsJSReceiver(*object)) {
1736 return Object::CannotCreateProperty(isolate, object, key.GetName(isolate),
1737 value, Nothing<ShouldThrow>());
1738 }
1739 return CreateDataProperty(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(object), key, value,
1740 should_throw);
1741}
1742
1743// static
1744Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1745 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
1746 PropertyKey key,
1747 DirectHandle<Object> value,
1748 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1749 if (IsJSObject(*object)) {
1750 return JSObject::CreateDataProperty(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object), key,
1751 value, should_throw); // Shortcut.
1752 }
1753
1754 PropertyDescriptor new_desc;
1755 new_desc.set_value(Cast<JSAny>(value));
1756 new_desc.set_writable(true);
1757 new_desc.set_enumerable(true);
1758 new_desc.set_configurable(true);
1759
1760 return JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, object, key.GetName(isolate),
1761 &new_desc, should_throw);
1762}
1763
1764// static
1765Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::AddPrivateField(LookupIterator* it,
1766 DirectHandle<Object> value,
1767 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1768 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(it->GetReceiver());
1769 DCHECK(!IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*receiver));
1770 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1771 DCHECK(it->GetName()->IsPrivateName());
1772 DirectHandle<Symbol> symbol = Cast<Symbol>(it->GetName());
1773
1774 switch (it->state()) {
1775 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
1776 PropertyDescriptor new_desc;
1777 new_desc.set_value(Cast<JSAny>(value));
1778 new_desc.set_writable(true);
1779 new_desc.set_enumerable(true);
1780 new_desc.set_configurable(true);
1781 return JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol(isolate, Cast<JSProxy>(receiver), symbol,
1782 &new_desc, should_throw);
1783 }
1784 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1785 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
1786 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
1787 case LookupIterator::DATA:
1788 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
1789 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1790 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1791 UNREACHABLE();
1792
1793 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK: {
1794 if (!it->HasAccess()) {
1795 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1796 isolate,
1797 it->isolate()->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it->GetHolder<JSObject>()),
1798 Nothing<bool>());
1799 UNREACHABLE();
1800 }
1801 break;
1802 }
1803
1804 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1805 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1806 break;
1807 }
1808
1809 return Object::TransitionAndWriteDataProperty(it, value, NONE, should_throw,
1810 StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed);
1811}
1812
1813// static
1814Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
1815 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object, DirectHandle<Object> key,
1816 PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
1817 DCHECK(IsName(*key) || IsNumber(*key)); // |key| is a PropertyKey.
1818 PropertyKey lookup_key(isolate, key);
1819 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, lookup_key, LookupIterator::OWN);
1820 return GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(&it, desc);
1821}
1822
1823namespace {
1824
1825Maybe<bool> GetPropertyDescriptorWithInterceptor(LookupIterator* it,
1826 PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
1827 DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor;
1828
1829 while (it->state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
1830 if (it->HasAccess()) {
1831 it->Next();
1832 } else {
1833 interceptor = it->GetInterceptorForFailedAccessCheck();
1834 if (interceptor.is_null()) {
1835 it->Restart();
1836 return Just(false);
1837 }
1838 CHECK(!interceptor.is_null());
1839 break;
1840 }
1841 }
1842 if (it->state() == LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR) {
1843 interceptor = it->GetInterceptor();
1844 }
1845 if (interceptor.is_null()) return Just(false);
1846 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1847 if (IsUndefined(interceptor->descriptor(), isolate)) return Just(false);
1848
1849 Handle<JSAny> result;
1850 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1851
1852 DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1853 if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1854 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
1855 Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1856 Nothing<bool>());
1857 }
1858
1859 PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1860 *holder, Just(kDontThrow));
1861 if (it->IsElement(*holder)) {
1862 result = args.CallIndexedDescriptor(interceptor, it->array_index());
1863 } else {
1864 result = args.CallNamedDescriptor(interceptor, it->name());
1865 }
1866 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1867 RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, args, Nothing<bool>());
1868 if (!result.is_null()) {
1869 // Request was successfully intercepted, try to set the property
1870 // descriptor.
1871 args.AcceptSideEffects();
1872 Utils::ApiCheck(
1873 PropertyDescriptor::ToPropertyDescriptor(isolate, result, desc),
1874 it->IsElement(*holder) ? "v8::IndexedPropertyDescriptorCallback"
1875 : "v8::NamedPropertyDescriptorCallback",
1876 "Invalid property descriptor.");
1877
1878 return Just(true);
1879 }
1880
1881 it->Next();
1882 return Just(false);
1883}
1884} // namespace
1885
1886// ES6 9.1.5.1
1887// Returns true on success, false if the property didn't exist, nothing if
1888// an exception was thrown.
1889// static
1890Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(LookupIterator* it,
1891 PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
1892 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1893 // "Virtual" dispatch.
1894 if (it->IsFound() && IsJSProxy(*it->GetHolder<JSReceiver>())) {
1895 return JSProxy::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
1896 it->GetName(), desc);
1897 }
1898
1899 Maybe<bool> intercepted = GetPropertyDescriptorWithInterceptor(it, desc);
1900 MAYBE_RETURN(intercepted, Nothing<bool>());
1901 if (intercepted.FromJust()) {
1902 return Just(true);
1903 }
1904
1905 // Request was not intercepted, continue as normal.
1906 // 1. (Assert)
1907 // 2. If O does not have an own property with key P, return undefined.
1908 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> maybe = JSObject::GetPropertyAttributes(it);
1909 MAYBE_RETURN(maybe, Nothing<bool>());
1910 PropertyAttributes attrs = maybe.FromJust();
1911 if (attrs == ABSENT) return Just(false);
1912 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
1913
1914 // 3. Let D be a newly created Property Descriptor with no fields.
1915 DCHECK(desc->is_empty());
1916 // 4. Let X be O's own property whose key is P.
1917 // 5. If X is a data property, then
1918 bool is_accessor_pair = it->state() == LookupIterator::ACCESSOR &&
1919 IsAccessorPair(*it->GetAccessors());
1920 if (!is_accessor_pair) {
1921 // 5a. Set D.[[Value]] to the value of X's [[Value]] attribute.
1922 DirectHandle<JSAny> value;
1923 if (!Cast<JSAny>(Object::GetProperty(it)).ToHandle(&value)) {
1924 DCHECK(isolate->has_exception());
1925 return Nothing<bool>();
1926 }
1927 desc->set_value(value);
1928 // 5b. Set D.[[Writable]] to the value of X's [[Writable]] attribute
1929 desc->set_writable((attrs & READ_ONLY) == 0);
1930 } else {
1931 // 6. Else X is an accessor property, so
1932 auto accessors = Cast<AccessorPair>(it->GetAccessors());
1933 DirectHandle<NativeContext> holder_realm(
1934 it->GetHolder<JSReceiver>()->GetCreationContext().value(), isolate);
1935 // 6a. Set D.[[Get]] to the value of X's [[Get]] attribute.
1936 desc->set_get(AccessorPair::GetComponent(isolate, holder_realm, accessors,
1937 ACCESSOR_GETTER));
1938 // 6b. Set D.[[Set]] to the value of X's [[Set]] attribute.
1939 desc->set_set(AccessorPair::GetComponent(isolate, holder_realm, accessors,
1940 ACCESSOR_SETTER));
1941 }
1942
1943 // 7. Set D.[[Enumerable]] to the value of X's [[Enumerable]] attribute.
1944 desc->set_enumerable((attrs & DONT_ENUM) == 0);
1945 // 8. Set D.[[Configurable]] to the value of X's [[Configurable]] attribute.
1946 desc->set_configurable((attrs & DONT_DELETE) == 0);
1947 // 9. Return D.
1948 DCHECK(PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(desc) !=
1949 PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(desc));
1950 return Just(true);
1951}
1952
1953Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::SetIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate,
1954 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
1955 IntegrityLevel level,
1956 ShouldThrow should_throw) {
1957 DCHECK(level == SEALED || level == FROZEN);
1958
1959 if (IsJSObject(*receiver)) {
1960 DirectHandle<JSObject> object = Cast<JSObject>(receiver);
1961
1962 if (!object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements() &&
1963 !IsJSModuleNamespace(*object)) { // Fast path.
1964 // Prevent memory leaks by not adding unnecessary transitions.
1965 Maybe<bool> test = JSObject::TestIntegrityLevel(isolate, object, level);
1966 MAYBE_RETURN(test, Nothing<bool>());
1967 if (test.FromJust()) return test;
1968
1969 if (level == SEALED) {
1970 return JSObject::PreventExtensionsWithTransition<SEALED>(
1971 isolate, object, should_throw);
1972 } else {
1973 return JSObject::PreventExtensionsWithTransition<FROZEN>(
1974 isolate, object, should_throw);
1975 }
1976 }
1977 }
1978
1979 MAYBE_RETURN(JSReceiver::PreventExtensions(isolate, receiver, should_throw),
1980 Nothing<bool>());
1981
1982 DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
1983 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1984 isolate, keys, JSReceiver::OwnPropertyKeys(isolate, receiver),
1985 Nothing<bool>());
1986
1987 PropertyDescriptor no_conf;
1988 no_conf.set_configurable(false);
1989
1990 PropertyDescriptor no_conf_no_write;
1991 no_conf_no_write.set_configurable(false);
1992 no_conf_no_write.set_writable(false);
1993
1994 if (level == SEALED) {
1995 for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
1996 DirectHandle<Object> key(keys->get(i), isolate);
1997 MAYBE_RETURN(DefineOwnProperty(isolate, receiver, key, &no_conf,
1998 Just(kThrowOnError)),
1999 Nothing<bool>());
2000 }
2001 return Just(true);
2002 }
2003
2004 for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
2005 DirectHandle<Object> key(keys->get(i), isolate);
2006 PropertyDescriptor current_desc;
2007 Maybe<bool> owned = JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
2008 isolate, receiver, key, &current_desc);
2009 MAYBE_RETURN(owned, Nothing<bool>());
2010 if (owned.FromJust()) {
2011 PropertyDescriptor desc =
2012 PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(&current_desc)
2013 ? no_conf
2014 : no_conf_no_write;
2015 MAYBE_RETURN(
2016 DefineOwnProperty(isolate, receiver, key, &desc, Just(kThrowOnError)),
2017 Nothing<bool>());
2018 }
2019 }
2020 return Just(true);
2021}
2022
2023namespace {
2024Maybe<bool> GenericTestIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate,
2025 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
2026 PropertyAttributes level) {
2027 DCHECK(level == SEALED || level == FROZEN);
2028
2029 Maybe<bool> extensible = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, receiver);
2030 MAYBE_RETURN(extensible, Nothing<bool>());
2031 if (extensible.FromJust()) return Just(false);
2032
2033 DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
2034 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2035 isolate, keys, JSReceiver::OwnPropertyKeys(isolate, receiver),
2036 Nothing<bool>());
2037
2038 for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
2039 DirectHandle<Object> key(keys->get(i), isolate);
2040 PropertyDescriptor current_desc;
2041 Maybe<bool> owned = JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
2042 isolate, receiver, key, &current_desc);
2043 MAYBE_RETURN(owned, Nothing<bool>());
2044 if (owned.FromJust()) {
2045 if (current_desc.configurable()) return Just(false);
2046 if (level == FROZEN &&
2047 PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(&current_desc) &&
2048 current_desc.writable()) {
2049 return Just(false);
2050 }
2051 }
2052 }
2053 return Just(true);
2054}
2055
2056} // namespace
2057
2058Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::TestIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate,
2059 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
2060 IntegrityLevel level) {
2061 if (!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(receiver->map())) {
2062 return JSObject::TestIntegrityLevel(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(receiver),
2063 level);
2064 }
2065 return GenericTestIntegrityLevel(isolate, receiver, level);
2066}
2067
2068Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::PreventExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
2069 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
2070 ShouldThrow should_throw) {
2071 if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
2072 return JSProxy::PreventExtensions(Cast<JSProxy>(object), should_throw);
2073 }
2074 if (IsWasmObject(*object)) {
2075 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
2076 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
2077 }
2078 DCHECK(IsJSObject(*object));
2079 return JSObject::PreventExtensions(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object),
2080 should_throw);
2081}
2082
2083Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::IsExtensible(Isolate* isolate,
2084 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object) {
2085 if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
2086 return JSProxy::IsExtensible(Cast<JSProxy>(object));
2087 }
2088 if (IsWasmObject(*object)) {
2089 return Just(false);
2090 }
2091 return Just(JSObject::IsExtensible(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object)));
2092}
