2094// static
2095template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
2096 requires(
2097 std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<JSReceiver>, DirectHandle<JSReceiver>>)
2098typename HandleType<Object>::MaybeType JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(
2099 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<JSReceiver> receiver, ToPrimitiveHint hint) {
2100 HandleType<Object> exotic_to_prim;
2101 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2102 isolate, exotic_to_prim,
2103 Object::GetMethod(isolate, receiver,
2104 isolate->factory()->to_primitive_symbol()));
2105 if (!IsUndefined(*exotic_to_prim, isolate)) {
2106 DirectHandle<Object> hint_string =
2107 isolate->factory()->ToPrimitiveHintString(hint);
2108 HandleType<Object> result;
2109 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2110 isolate, result,
2111 Execution::Call(isolate, exotic_to_prim, receiver, {&hint_string, 1}));
2112 if (IsPrimitive(*result)) return result;
2113 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
2114 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotConvertToPrimitive));
2115 }
2116 return OrdinaryToPrimitive(isolate, receiver,
2117 (hint == ToPrimitiveHint::kString)
2118 ? OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kString
2119 : OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kNumber);
2120}
2121
2122template MaybeDirectHandle<Object> JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(
2123 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver, ToPrimitiveHint hint);
2124template MaybeIndirectHandle<Object> JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(
2125 Isolate* isolate, IndirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
2126 ToPrimitiveHint hint);
2127
2128// static
2129MaybeHandle<Object> JSReceiver::OrdinaryToPrimitive(
2130 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
2131 OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint hint) {
2132 DirectHandle<String> method_names[2];
2133 switch (hint) {
2134 case OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kNumber:
2135 method_names[0] = isolate->factory()->valueOf_string();
2136 method_names[1] = isolate->factory()->toString_string();
2137 break;
2138 case OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kString:
2139 method_names[0] = isolate->factory()->toString_string();
2140 method_names[1] = isolate->factory()->valueOf_string();
2141 break;
2142 }
2143 for (DirectHandle<String> name : method_names) {
2144 DirectHandle<Object> method;
2145 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2146 isolate, method, JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, receiver, name));
2147 if (IsCallable(*method)) {
2148 Handle<Object> result;
2149 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2150 isolate, result, Execution::Call(isolate, method, receiver, {}));
2151 if (IsPrimitive(*result)) return result;
2152 }
2153 }
2154 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
2155 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotConvertToPrimitive));
2156}
2157
2158V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> FastGetOwnValuesOrEntries(
2159 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver, bool get_entries,
2160 Handle<FixedArray>* result) {
2161 DirectHandle<Map> map(Cast<JSReceiver>(*receiver)->map(), isolate);
2162
2163 if (!IsJSObjectMap(*map)) return Just(false);
2164 if (!map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties()) return Just(false);
2165
2166 DirectHandle<JSObject> object(Cast<JSObject>(*receiver), isolate);
2167 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descriptors(map->instance_descriptors(isolate),
2168 isolate);
2169
2170 int number_of_own_descriptors = map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
2171 size_t number_of_own_elements =
2172 object->GetElementsAccessor()->GetCapacity(*object, object->elements());
2173
2174 if (number_of_own_elements >
2175 static_cast<size_t>(FixedArray::kMaxLength - number_of_own_descriptors)) {
2176 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewRangeError(
2177 MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength));
2178 return Nothing<bool>();
2179 }
2180 // The static cast is safe after the range check right above.
2181 Handle<FixedArray> values_or_entries = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(
2182 static_cast<int>(number_of_own_descriptors + number_of_own_elements));
2183 int count = 0;
2184
2185 if (object->elements() != ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array()) {
2186 MAYBE_RETURN(object->GetElementsAccessor()->CollectValuesOrEntries(
2187 isolate, object, values_or_entries, get_entries, &count,
2188 ENUMERABLE_STRINGS),
2189 Nothing<bool>());
2190 }
2191
2192 // We may have already lost stability, if CollectValuesOrEntries had
2193 // side-effects.
2194 bool stable = *map == object->map();
2195 if (stable) {
2196 descriptors.SetValue(map->instance_descriptors(isolate));
2197 }
2198
2199 for (InternalIndex index : InternalIndex::Range(number_of_own_descriptors)) {
2200 HandleScope inner_scope(isolate);
2201
2202 DirectHandle<Name> next_key(descriptors->GetKey(index), isolate);
2203 if (!IsString(*next_key)) continue;
2204 DirectHandle<Object> prop_value;
2205
2206 // Directly decode from the descriptor array if |from| did not change shape.
2207 if (stable) {
2208 DCHECK_EQ(object->map(), *map);
2209 DCHECK_EQ(*descriptors, map->instance_descriptors(isolate));
2210
2211 PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(index);
2212 if (!details.IsEnumerable()) continue;
2213 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
2214 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kDescriptor) {
2215 prop_value =
2216 direct_handle(descriptors->GetStrongValue(index), isolate);
2217 } else {
2218 Representation representation = details.representation();
2219 FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(
2220 *map, details.field_index(), representation);
2221 prop_value = JSObject::FastPropertyAt(isolate, object, representation,
2222 field_index);
2223 }
2224 } else {
2225 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, next_key,
2226 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
2227 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::ACCESSOR, it.state());
2228 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2229 isolate, prop_value, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
2230 stable = object->map() == *map;
2231 descriptors.SetValue(map->instance_descriptors(isolate));
2232 }
2233 } else {
2234 // If the map did change, do a slower lookup. We are still guaranteed that
2235 // the object has a simple shape, and that the key is a name.
2236 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, next_key,
2237 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
2238 if (!it.IsFound()) continue;
2239 DCHECK(it.state() == LookupIterator::DATA ||
2240 it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESSOR);
2241 if (!it.IsEnumerable()) continue;
2242 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2243 isolate, prop_value, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
2244 }
2245
2246 if (get_entries) {
2247 prop_value = MakeEntryPair(isolate, next_key, prop_value);
2248 }
2249
2250 values_or_entries->set(count, *prop_value);
2251 count++;
2252 }
2253
2254 DCHECK_LE(count, values_or_entries->length());
2255 *result = FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, values_or_entries, count);
2256 return Just(true);
2257}
2258
2259MaybeHandle<FixedArray> GetOwnValuesOrEntries(Isolate* isolate,
2260 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
2261 PropertyFilter filter,
2262 bool try_fast_path,
2263 bool get_entries) {
2264 Handle<FixedArray> values_or_entries;
2265 if (try_fast_path && filter == ENUMERABLE_STRINGS) {
2266 Maybe<bool> fast_values_or_entries = FastGetOwnValuesOrEntries(
2267 isolate, object, get_entries, &values_or_entries);
2268 if (fast_values_or_entries.IsNothing()) return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
2269 if (fast_values_or_entries.FromJust()) return values_or_entries;
2270 }
2271
2272 PropertyFilter key_filter =
2273 static_cast<PropertyFilter>(filter & ~ONLY_ENUMERABLE);
2274
2275 DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
2276 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2277 isolate, keys,
2278 KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, object, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
2279 key_filter, GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString),
2280 MaybeHandle<FixedArray>());
2281
2282 values_or_entries = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(keys->length());
2283 int length = 0;
2284
2285 for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
2286 DirectHandle<Name> key(Cast<Name>(keys->get(i)), isolate);
2287
2288 if (filter & ONLY_ENUMERABLE) {
2289 PropertyDescriptor descriptor;
2290 Maybe<bool> did_get_descriptor = JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
2291 isolate, object, key, &descriptor);
2292 MAYBE_RETURN(did_get_descriptor, MaybeHandle<FixedArray>());
2293 if (!did_get_descriptor.FromJust() || !descriptor.enumerable()) continue;
2294 }
2295
2296 DirectHandle<Object> value;
2297 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2298 isolate, value, Object::GetPropertyOrElement(isolate, object, key),
2299 MaybeHandle<FixedArray>());
2300
2301 if (get_entries) {
2302 DirectHandle<FixedArray> entry_storage =
2303 isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(2);
2304 entry_storage->set(0, *key);
2305 entry_storage->set(1, *value);
2306 value = isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayWithElements(entry_storage,
2307 PACKED_ELEMENTS, 2);
2308 }
2309
2310 values_or_entries->set(length, *value);
2311 length++;
2312 }
2313 DCHECK_LE(length, values_or_entries->length());
2314 return FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, values_or_entries, length);
2315}
2316
2317MaybeHandle<FixedArray> JSReceiver::GetOwnValues(
2318 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object, PropertyFilter filter,
2319 bool try_fast_path) {
2320 return GetOwnValuesOrEntries(isolate, object, filter, try_fast_path, false);
2321}
2322
2323MaybeHandle<FixedArray> JSReceiver::GetOwnEntries(
2324 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object, PropertyFilter filter,
2325 bool try_fast_path) {
2326 return GetOwnValuesOrEntries(isolate, object, filter, try_fast_path, true);
2327}

2329Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::SetPrototype(Isolate* isolate,
2330 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
2331 DirectHandle<Object> value,
2332 bool from_javascript,
2333 ShouldThrow should_throw) {
2334 if (IsWasmObject(*object)) {
2335 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
2336 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
2337 }
2338
2339 if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
2340 return JSProxy::SetPrototype(isolate, Cast<JSProxy>(object), value,
2341 from_javascript, should_throw);
2342 }
2343 return JSObject::SetPrototype(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object), value,
2344 from_javascript, should_throw);
2345}

2347bool JSReceiver::HasProxyInPrototype(Isolate* isolate) {
2348 for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, *this, kStartAtReceiver,
2349 PrototypeIterator::END_AT_NULL);
2350 !iter.IsAtEnd(); iter.AdvanceIgnoringProxies()) {
2351 if (IsJSProxy(iter.GetCurrent())) return true;
2352 }
2353 return false;
2354}
2355
2356bool JSReceiver::IsCodeLike(Isolate* isolate) const {
2357 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2358 Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = map()->GetConstructor();
2359 if (!IsJSFunction(maybe_constructor)) return false;
2360 if (!Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor)->shared()->IsApiFunction()) {
2361 return false;
2362 }
2363 Tagged<Object> instance_template = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor)
2364 ->shared()
2365 ->api_func_data()
2366 ->GetInstanceTemplate();
2367 if (IsUndefined(instance_template, isolate)) return false;
2368 return Cast<ObjectTemplateInfo>(instance_template)->code_like();
2369}

2371// static
2372MaybeHandle<JSObject> JSObject::New(DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor,
2373 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> new_target,
2374 DirectHandle<AllocationSite> site,
2375 NewJSObjectType new_js_object_type) {
2376 // If called through new, new.target can be:
2377 // - a subclass of constructor,
2378 // - a proxy wrapper around constructor, or
2379 // - the constructor itself.
2380 // If called through Reflect.construct, it's guaranteed to be a constructor.
2381 Isolate* const isolate = constructor->GetIsolate();
2382 DCHECK(IsConstructor(*constructor));
2383 DCHECK(IsConstructor(*new_target));
2384 DCHECK(!constructor->has_initial_map() ||
2385 !InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(
2386 constructor->initial_map()->instance_type()));
2387
2388 DirectHandle<Map> initial_map;
2389 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2390 isolate, initial_map,
2391 JSFunction::GetDerivedMap(isolate, constructor, new_target));
2392 constexpr int initial_capacity = PropertyDictionary::kInitialCapacity;
2393 Handle<JSObject> result = isolate->factory()->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(
2394 initial_map, initial_capacity, AllocationType::kYoung, site,
2395 new_js_object_type);
2396 return result;
2397}
2398
2399// static
2400MaybeHandle<JSObject> JSObject::NewWithMap(Isolate* isolate,
2401 DirectHandle<Map> initial_map,
2402 DirectHandle<AllocationSite> site,
2403 NewJSObjectType new_js_object_type) {
2404 constexpr int initial_capacity = PropertyDictionary::kInitialCapacity;
2405 Handle<JSObject> result = isolate->factory()->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(
2406 initial_map, initial_capacity, AllocationType::kYoung, site,
2407 new_js_object_type);
2408 return result;
2409}

2411// 9.1.12 ObjectCreate ( proto [ , internalSlotsList ] )
2412// Notice: This is NOT 19.1.2.2 Object.create ( O, Properties )
2413MaybeHandle<JSObject> JSObject::ObjectCreate(
2414 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSPrototype> prototype) {
2415 // Generate the map with the specified {prototype} based on the Object
2416 // function's initial map from the current native context.
2417 // TODO(bmeurer): Use a dedicated cache for Object.create; think about
2418 // slack tracking for Object.create.
2419 DirectHandle<Map> map = Map::GetObjectCreateMap(isolate, prototype);
2420
2421 // Actually allocate the object.
2422 return isolate->factory()->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(map);
2423}
2424
2425void JSObject::EnsureWritableFastElements(DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
2426 DCHECK(object->HasSmiOrObjectElements() ||
2427 object->HasFastStringWrapperElements() ||
2428 object->HasAnyNonextensibleElements());
2429 Tagged<FixedArray> raw_elems = Cast<FixedArray>(object->elements());
2430 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
2431 if (raw_elems->map() != ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).fixed_cow_array_map()) return;
2432 DirectHandle<FixedArray> elems(raw_elems, isolate);
2433 DirectHandle<FixedArray> writable_elems =
2434 isolate->factory()->CopyFixedArrayWithMap(
2435 elems, isolate->factory()->fixed_array_map());
2436 object->set_elements(*writable_elems);
2437}

2439// For FATAL in JSObject::GetHeaderSize
2440static const char* NonAPIInstanceTypeToString(InstanceType instance_type) {
2441 DCHECK(!InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(instance_type));
2442 switch (instance_type) {
2443#define WRITE_TYPE(TYPE) \
2444 case TYPE: \
2445 return #TYPE;
2446 INSTANCE_TYPE_LIST(WRITE_TYPE)
2447#undef WRITE_TYPE
2448 }
2449 UNREACHABLE();
2450}
2451
2452int JSObject::GetHeaderSize(InstanceType type,
2453 bool function_has_prototype_slot) {
2454 switch (type) {
2455 case JS_SPECIAL_API_OBJECT_TYPE:
2456 case JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE:
2457 return JSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlots::BodyDescriptor::kHeaderSize;
2458 case JS_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2459 case JS_MAP_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2460 case JS_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2461 case JS_OBJECT_TYPE:
2462 case JS_PROMISE_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2463 case JS_REG_EXP_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2464 case JS_SET_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2465 case JS_SET_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2466 case JS_STRING_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2467 case JS_ARRAY_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2468 case JS_TYPED_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
2469 case JS_CONTEXT_EXTENSION_OBJECT_TYPE:
2470 case JS_ARGUMENTS_OBJECT_TYPE:
2471 case JS_ERROR_TYPE:
2472 return JSObject::kHeaderSize;
2473 case JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE:
2474 return JSGeneratorObject::kHeaderSize;
2475 case JS_ASYNC_FUNCTION_OBJECT_TYPE:
2476 return JSAsyncFunctionObject::kHeaderSize;
2477 case JS_ASYNC_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE:
2478 return JSAsyncGeneratorObject::kHeaderSize;
2479 case JS_ASYNC_FROM_SYNC_ITERATOR_TYPE:
2480 return JSAsyncFromSyncIterator::kHeaderSize;
2481 case JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE:
2482 return JSGlobalProxy::kHeaderSize;
2483 case JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE:
2484 return JSGlobalObject::kHeaderSize;
2485 case JS_BOUND_FUNCTION_TYPE:
2486 return JSBoundFunction::kHeaderSize;
2487 case JS_FUNCTION_TYPE:
2488 case JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2489 case JS_PROMISE_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2490 case JS_REG_EXP_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2491 case JS_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2492#define TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH(Type, type, TYPE, Ctype) \
2493 case TYPE##_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2494 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH)
2495#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH
2496 return JSFunction::GetHeaderSize(function_has_prototype_slot);
2497 case JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE:
2498 return JSPrimitiveWrapper::kHeaderSize;
2499 case JS_DATE_TYPE:
2500 return JSDate::kHeaderSize;
2501 case JS_DISPOSABLE_STACK_BASE_TYPE:
2502 return JSDisposableStackBase::kHeaderSize;
2503 case JS_ASYNC_DISPOSABLE_STACK_TYPE:
2504 return JSAsyncDisposableStack::kHeaderSize;
2505 case JS_SYNC_DISPOSABLE_STACK_TYPE:

2658
2659MaybeHandle<JSAny> JSObject::GetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(
2660 LookupIterator* it) {
2661 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2662 DirectHandle<JSObject> checked = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2663 DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor =
2664 it->GetInterceptorForFailedAccessCheck();
2665 if (!interceptor.is_null()) {
2666 Handle<JSAny> result;
2667 bool done;
2668 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2669 isolate, result,
2670 GetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(it, interceptor, &done));
2671 if (done) return result;
2672 }
2673
2674 // Cross-Origin [[Get]] of Well-Known Symbols does not throw, and returns
2675 // undefined.
2676 DirectHandle<Name> name = it->GetName();
2677 if (IsSymbol(*name) && Cast<Symbol>(*name)->is_well_known_symbol()) {
2678 return it->factory()->undefined_value();
2679 }
2680
2681 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(checked));
2682 UNREACHABLE();
2683}
2684
2685Maybe<PropertyAttributes> JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithFailedAccessCheck(
2686 LookupIterator* it) {
2687 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2688 DirectHandle<JSObject> checked = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2689 DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor =
2690 it->GetInterceptorForFailedAccessCheck();
2691 if (!interceptor.is_null()) {
2692 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> result =
2693 GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptorInternal(it, interceptor);
2694 if (isolate->has_exception()) return Nothing<PropertyAttributes>();
2695 if (result.FromMaybe(ABSENT) != ABSENT) return result;
2696 }
2697 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(checked),
2698 Nothing<PropertyAttributes>());
2699 UNREACHABLE();
2700}
2701
2702Maybe<bool> JSObject::SetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(
2703 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2704 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2705 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2706 DirectHandle<JSObject> checked = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2707 DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor =
2708 it->GetInterceptorForFailedAccessCheck();
2709 if (!interceptor.is_null()) {
2710 InterceptorResult result;
2711 if (!SetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(it, interceptor, should_throw,
2712 value)
2713 .To(&result)) {
2714 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
2715 return Nothing<bool>();
2716 }
2717 switch (result) {
2718 case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
2719 return Just(false);
2720 case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
2721 return Just(true);
2722 case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
2723 // Fall through to report failed access check.
2724 break;
2725 }
2726 }
2727 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(checked),
2728 Nothing<bool>());
2729 UNREACHABLE();
2730}
2731
2732void JSObject::SetNormalizedProperty(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
2733 DirectHandle<Name> name,
2734 DirectHandle<Object> value,
2735 PropertyDetails details) {
2736 DCHECK(!object->HasFastProperties());
2737 DCHECK(IsUniqueName(*name));
2738 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
2739
2740 uint32_t hash = name->hash();
2741
2742 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*object)) {
2743 auto global_obj = Cast<JSGlobalObject>(object);
2744 DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary(
2745 global_obj->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad), isolate);
2746 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2747 InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, roots, name, hash);
2748
2749 if (entry.is_not_found()) {
2750 DCHECK_IMPLIES(global_obj->map()->is_prototype_map(),
2751 Map::IsPrototypeChainInvalidated(global_obj->map()));
2752 auto cell_type = IsUndefined(*value, roots) ? PropertyCellType::kUndefined
2753 : PropertyCellType::kConstant;
2754 details = details.set_cell_type(cell_type);
2755 auto cell = isolate->factory()->NewPropertyCell(name, details, value);
2756 dictionary =
2757 GlobalDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, name, cell, details);
2758 global_obj->set_global_dictionary(*dictionary, kReleaseStore);
2759 } else {
2760 PropertyCell::PrepareForAndSetValue(isolate, dictionary, entry, value,
2761 details);
2762 DCHECK_EQ(dictionary->CellAt(entry)->value(), *value);
2763 }
2764 } else {
2765 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
2766 DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> dictionary(
2767 object->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate);
2768 InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, *name);
2769 if (entry.is_not_found()) {
2770 DCHECK_IMPLIES(object->map()->is_prototype_map(),
2771 Map::IsPrototypeChainInvalidated(object->map()));
2772 dictionary =
2773 SwissNameDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, name, value, details);
2774 object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
2775 } else {
2776 dictionary->ValueAtPut(entry, *value);
2777 dictionary->DetailsAtPut(entry, details);
2778 }
2779 } else {
2780 DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary(object->property_dictionary(),
2781 isolate);
2782 InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, name);
2783 if (entry.is_not_found()) {
2784 DCHECK_IMPLIES(object->map()->is_prototype_map(),
2785 Map::IsPrototypeChainInvalidated(object->map()));
2786 dictionary =
2787 NameDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, name, value, details);
2788 object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
2789 } else {
2790 PropertyDetails original_details = dictionary->DetailsAt(entry);
2791 int enumeration_index = original_details.dictionary_index();
2792 DCHECK_GT(enumeration_index, 0);
2793 details = details.set_index(enumeration_index);
2794 dictionary->SetEntry(entry, *name, *value, details);
2795 }
2796 // TODO(pthier): Add flags to swiss dictionaries.
2797 if (name->IsInteresting(isolate)) {
2798 dictionary->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
2799 }
2800 }
2801 }
2802}
2803
2804void JSObject::SetNormalizedElement(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
2805 uint32_t index, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2806 PropertyDetails details) {
2807 DCHECK_EQ(object->GetElementsKind(), DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS);
2808
2809 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
2810
2811 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary(
2812 Cast<NumberDictionary>(object->elements()), isolate);
2813 dictionary =
2814 NumberDictionary::Set(isolate, dictionary, index, value, object, details);
2815 object->set_elements(*dictionary);
2816}
2817
2818void JSObject::JSObjectShortPrint(StringStream* accumulator) {
2819 switch (map()->instance_type()) {
2820 case JS_ARRAY_TYPE: {
2821 double length = IsUndefined(Cast<JSArray>(*this)->length())
2822 ? 0
2823 : Object::NumberValue(Cast<JSArray>(*this)->length());
2824 accumulator->Add("<JSArray[%u]>", static_cast<uint32_t>(length));
2825 break;
2826 }
2827 case JS_BOUND_FUNCTION_TYPE: {
2828 Tagged<JSBoundFunction> bound_function = Cast<JSBoundFunction>(*this);
2829 accumulator->Add("<JSBoundFunction");
2830 accumulator->Add(" (BoundTargetFunction %p)>",
2831 reinterpret_cast<void*>(
2832 bound_function->bound_target_function().ptr()));
2833 break;
2834 }
2835 case JS_WEAK_MAP_TYPE: {
2836 accumulator->Add("<JSWeakMap>");
2837 break;
2838 }
2839 case JS_WEAK_SET_TYPE: {
2840 accumulator->Add("<JSWeakSet>");
2841 break;
2842 }
2843 case JS_REG_EXP_TYPE: {
2844 accumulator->Add("<JSRegExp");
2845 Tagged<JSRegExp> regexp = Cast<JSRegExp>(*this);
2846 if (IsString(regexp->source())) {
2847 accumulator->Add(" ");
2848 Cast<String>(regexp->source())->StringShortPrint(accumulator);
2849 }
2850 accumulator->Add(">");
2851
2852 break;
2853 }
2854 case JS_PROMISE_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2855 case JS_REG_EXP_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2856 case JS_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2857#define TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH(Type, type, TYPE, Ctype) \
2858 case TYPE##_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2859 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH)
2860#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH
2861 case JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2862 case JS_FUNCTION_TYPE: {
2863 Tagged<JSFunction> function = Cast<JSFunction>(*this);
2864 std::unique_ptr<char[]> fun_name = function->shared()->DebugNameCStr();
2865 if (fun_name[0] != '\0') {
2866 accumulator->Add("<JSFunction ");
2867 accumulator->Add(fun_name.get());
2868 } else {
2869 accumulator->Add("<JSFunction");
2870 }
2871 if (v8_flags.trace_file_names) {
2872 Tagged<Object> source_name =
2873 Cast<Script>(function->shared()->script())->name();
2874 if (IsString(source_name)) {
2875 Tagged<String> str = Cast<String>(source_name);
2876 if (str->length() > 0) {
2877 accumulator->Add(" <");
2878 accumulator->Put(str);
2879 accumulator->Add(">");
2880 }
2881 }
2882 }
2883 accumulator->Add(" (sfi = %p)",
2884 reinterpret_cast<void*>(function->shared().ptr()));
2885 accumulator->Put('>');
2886 break;
2887 }
2888 case JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE: {
2889 accumulator->Add("<JSGenerator>");
2890 break;
2891 }
2892 case JS_ASYNC_FUNCTION_OBJECT_TYPE: {
2893 accumulator->Add("<JSAsyncFunctionObject>");
2894 break;
2895 }
2896 case JS_ASYNC_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE: {
2897 accumulator->Add("<JS AsyncGenerator>");
2898 break;
2899 }
2900 case JS_SHARED_ARRAY_TYPE:
2901 accumulator->Add("<JSSharedArray>");
2902 break;
2903 case JS_SHARED_STRUCT_TYPE:
2904 accumulator->Add("<JSSharedStruct>");
2905 break;
2906 case JS_ATOMICS_MUTEX_TYPE:
2907 accumulator->Add("<JSAtomicsMutex>");
2908 break;
2909 case JS_ATOMICS_CONDITION_TYPE:
2910 accumulator->Add("<JSAtomicsCondition>");
2911 break;
2912 case JS_MESSAGE_OBJECT_TYPE:
2913 accumulator->Add("<JSMessageObject>");
2914 break;
2915 case JS_EXTERNAL_OBJECT_TYPE:
2916 accumulator->Add("<JSExternalObject>");
2917 break;
2918
2919 default: {
2920 Tagged<Map> map_of_this = map();
2921 Tagged<Object> constructor = map_of_this->GetConstructor();
2922 bool printed = false;
2923 bool is_global_proxy = IsJSGlobalProxy(*this);
2924 if (IsJSFunction(constructor)) {
2925 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi =
2926 Cast<JSFunction>(constructor)->shared();
2927 Tagged<String> constructor_name = sfi->Name();
2928 if (constructor_name->length() > 0) {
2929 accumulator->Add(is_global_proxy ? "<GlobalObject " : "<");
2930 accumulator->Put(constructor_name);
2931 accumulator->Add(" %smap = %p",
2932 map_of_this->is_deprecated() ? "deprecated-" : "",
2933 map_of_this);
2934 printed = true;
2935 }
2936 } else if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(constructor)) {
2937 accumulator->Add("<RemoteObject>");
2938 printed = true;
2939 }
2940 if (!printed) {
2941 accumulator->Add("<JS");
2942 if (is_global_proxy) {
2943 accumulator->Add("GlobalProxy");
2944 } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(*this)) {
2945 accumulator->Add("GlobalObject");
2946 } else {
2947 accumulator->Add("Object");
2948 }
2949 }
2950 if (IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*this)) {
2951 accumulator->Add(" value = ");
2952 ShortPrint(Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(*this)->value(), accumulator);
2953 }
2954 accumulator->Put('>');
2955 break;
2956 }
2957 }
2958}
2959
2960void JSObject::PrintElementsTransition(
2961 FILE* file, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, ElementsKind from_kind,
2962 DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> from_elements, ElementsKind to_kind,
2963 DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> to_elements) {
2964 if (from_kind != to_kind) {
2965 OFStream os(file);
2966 os << "elements transition [" << ElementsKindToString(from_kind) << " -> "
2967 << ElementsKindToString(to_kind) << "] in ";
2968 JavaScriptFrame::PrintTop(object->GetIsolate(), file, false, true);
2969 PrintF(file, " for ");
2970 ShortPrint(*object, file);
2971 PrintF(file, " from ");
2972 ShortPrint(*from_elements, file);
2973 PrintF(file, " to ");
2974 ShortPrint(*to_elements, file);
2975 PrintF(file, "\n");
2976 }
2977}
2978
2979void JSObject::PrintInstanceMigration(FILE* file, Tagged<Map> original_map,
2980 Tagged<Map> new_map) {
2981 if (new_map->is_dictionary_map()) {
2982 PrintF(file, "[migrating to slow]\n");
2983 return;
2984 }
2985 PrintF(file, "[migrating]");
2986 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolate();
2987 Tagged<DescriptorArray> o = original_map->instance_descriptors(isolate);
2988 Tagged<DescriptorArray> n = new_map->instance_descriptors(isolate);
2989 for (InternalIndex i : original_map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
2990 Representation o_r = o->GetDetails(i).representation();
2991 Representation n_r = n->GetDetails(i).representation();
2992 if (!o_r.Equals(n_r)) {
2993 Cast<String>(o->GetKey(i))->PrintOn(file);
2994 PrintF(file, ":%s->%s ", o_r.Mnemonic(), n_r.Mnemonic());
2995 } else if (o->GetDetails(i).location() == PropertyLocation::kDescriptor &&
2996 n->GetDetails(i).location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
2997 Tagged<Name> name = o->GetKey(i);
2998 if (IsString(name)) {
2999 Cast<String>(name)->PrintOn(file);
3000 } else {
3001 PrintF(file, "{symbol %p}", reinterpret_cast<void*>(name.ptr()));
3002 }
3003 PrintF(file, " ");
3004 }
3005 }
3006 if (original_map->elements_kind() != new_map->elements_kind()) {
3007 PrintF(file, "elements_kind[%i->%i]", original_map->elements_kind(),
3008 new_map->elements_kind());
3009 }
3010 PrintF(file, "\n");
3011}
3012
3013// static
3014bool JSObject::IsUnmodifiedApiObject(FullObjectSlot o) {
3015 Tagged<Object> object = *o;
3016 if (IsSmi(object)) return false;
3017 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
3018 Tagged<Map> map = heap_object->map();
3019 if (!InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(map)) return false;
3020 if (!JSObject::IsDroppableApiObject(map)) return false;
3021 Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = map->GetConstructor();
3022 if (!IsJSFunction(maybe_constructor)) return false;
3023 Tagged<JSObject> js_object = Cast<JSObject>(object);
3024 if (js_object->elements()->length() != 0) return false;
3025 // Check that the object is not a key in a WeakMap (over-approximation).
3026 if (!IsUndefined(js_object->GetIdentityHash())) return false;
3027
3028 Tagged<JSFunction> constructor = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
3029 return constructor->initial_map() == map;
3030}
3031
3032// static
3033void JSObject::UpdatePrototypeUserRegistration(DirectHandle<Map> old_map,
3034 DirectHandle<Map> new_map,
3035 Isolate* isolate) {
3036 DCHECK(old_map->is_prototype_map());
3037 DCHECK(new_map->is_prototype_map());
3038 bool was_registered = JSObject::UnregisterPrototypeUser(old_map, isolate);
3039 new_map->set_prototype_info(old_map->prototype_info(), kReleaseStore);
3040 old_map->set_prototype_info(Smi::zero(), kReleaseStore);
3041 if (v8_flags.trace_prototype_users) {
3042 PrintF("Moving prototype_info %p from map %p to map %p.\n",
3043 reinterpret_cast<void*>(new_map->prototype_info().ptr()),
3044 reinterpret_cast<void*>(old_map->ptr()),
3045 reinterpret_cast<void*>(new_map->ptr()));
3046 }
3047 if (was_registered) {
3048 if (new_map->has_prototype_info()) {
3049 // The new map isn't registered with its prototype yet; reflect this fact
3050 // in the PrototypeInfo it just inherited from the old map.
3051 Cast<PrototypeInfo>(new_map->prototype_info())
3052 ->set_registry_slot(MemoryChunk::UNREGISTERED);
3053 }
3054 JSObject::LazyRegisterPrototypeUser(new_map, isolate);
3055 }
3056}
3057
3058// static
3059void JSObject::NotifyMapChange(DirectHandle<Map> old_map,
3060 DirectHandle<Map> new_map, Isolate* isolate) {
3061 if (!old_map->is_prototype_map()) return;
3062
3063 InvalidatePrototypeChains(*old_map);
3064
3065 // If the map was registered with its prototype before, ensure that it
3066 // registers with its new prototype now. This preserves the invariant that
3067 // when a map on a prototype chain is registered with its prototype, then
3068 // all prototypes further up the chain are also registered with their
3069 // respective prototypes.
3070 UpdatePrototypeUserRegistration(old_map, new_map, isolate);
3071}
3072
3073namespace {
3074
3075// To migrate a fast instance to a fast map:
3076// - First check whether the instance needs to be rewritten. If not, simply
3077// change the map.
3078// - Otherwise, allocate a fixed array large enough to hold all fields, in
3079// addition to unused space.
3080// - Copy all existing properties in, in the following order: backing store
3081// properties, unused fields, inobject properties.
3082// - If all allocation succeeded, commit the state atomically:
3083// * Copy inobject properties from the backing store back into the object.
3084// * Trim the difference in instance size of the object. This also cleanly
3085// frees inobject properties that moved to the backing store.
3086// * If there are properties left in the backing store, trim of the space used
3087// to temporarily store the inobject properties.
3088// * If there are properties left in the backing store, install the backing
3089// store.
3090void MigrateFastToFast(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3091 DirectHandle<Map> new_map) {
3092 DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate);
3093 // In case of a regular transition.
3094 if (new_map->GetBackPointer(isolate) == *old_map) {
3095 // If the map does not add named properties, simply set the map.
3096 if (old_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() ==
3097 new_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors()) {
3098 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3099 return;
3100 }
3101
3102 // If the map adds a new kDescriptor property, simply set the map.
3103 PropertyDetails details = new_map->GetLastDescriptorDetails(isolate);
3104 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kDescriptor) {
3105 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3106 return;
3107 }
3108
3109 // Check if we still have space in the {object}, in which case we
3110 // can also simply set the map (modulo a special case for mutable
3111 // double boxes).
3112 FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(*new_map, details);
3113 if (index.is_inobject() || index.outobject_array_index() <
3114 object->property_array(isolate)->length()) {
3115 // Allocate HeapNumbers for double fields.
3116 if (index.is_double()) {
3117 auto value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3118 object->FastPropertyAtPut(index, *value);
3119 }
3120 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3121 return;
3122 }
3123
3124 // This migration is a transition from a map that has run out of property
3125 // space. Extend the backing store.
3126 int grow_by = new_map->UnusedPropertyFields() + 1;
3127 DirectHandle<PropertyArray> old_storage(object->property_array(isolate),
3128 isolate);
3129 DirectHandle<PropertyArray> new_storage =
3130 isolate->factory()->CopyPropertyArrayAndGrow(old_storage, grow_by);
3131
3132 // Properly initialize newly added property.
3133 DirectHandle<Object> value;
3134 if (details.representation().IsDouble()) {
3135 value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3136 } else {
3137 value = isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value();
3138 }
3139 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kField, details.location());
3140 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
3141 DCHECK(!index.is_inobject()); // Must be a backing store index.
3142 new_storage->set(index.outobject_array_index(), *value);
3143
3144 // From here on we cannot fail and we shouldn't GC anymore.
3145 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3146
3147 // Set the new property value and do the map transition.
3148 object->SetProperties(*new_storage);
3149 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3150 return;
3151 }
3152
3153 int old_number_of_fields;
3154 int number_of_fields = new_map->NumberOfFields(ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
3155 int inobject = new_map->GetInObjectProperties();
3156 int unused = new_map->UnusedPropertyFields();
3157
3158 // Nothing to do if no functions were converted to fields and no smis were
3159 // converted to doubles.
3160 if (!old_map->InstancesNeedRewriting(*new_map, number_of_fields, inobject,
3161 unused, &old_number_of_fields,
3162 ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous)) {
3163 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3164 return;
3165 }
3166
3167 int total_size = number_of_fields + unused;
3168 int external = total_size - inobject;
3169 DirectHandle<PropertyArray> array =
3170 isolate->factory()->NewPropertyArray(external);
3171
3172 // We use this array to temporarily store the inobject properties.
3173 DirectHandle<FixedArray> inobject_props =
3174 isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(inobject);
3175
3176 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> old_descriptors(
3177 old_map->instance_descriptors(isolate), isolate);
3178 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> new_descriptors(
3179 new_map->instance_descriptors(isolate), isolate);
3180 int old_nof = old_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
3181 int new_nof = new_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
3182
3183 // This method only supports generalizing instances to at least the same
3184 // number of properties.
3185 DCHECK(old_nof <= new_nof);
3186
3187 for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(old_nof)) {
3188 PropertyDetails details = new_descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3189 if (details.location() != PropertyLocation::kField) continue;
3190 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
3191 PropertyDetails old_details = old_descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3192 Representation old_representation = old_details.representation();
3193 Representation representation = details.representation();
3194 Handle<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>> value;
3195 if (old_details.location() == PropertyLocation::kDescriptor) {
3196 if (old_details.kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor) {
3197 // In case of kAccessor -> kData property reconfiguration, the property
3198 // must already be prepared for data of certain type.
3199 DCHECK(!details.representation().IsNone());
3200 if (details.representation().IsDouble()) {
3201 value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3202 } else {
3203 value = isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value();
3204 }
3205 } else {
3206 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, old_details.kind());
3207 value = handle(Cast<JSAny>(old_descriptors->GetStrongValue(isolate, i)),
3208 isolate);
3209 DCHECK(!old_representation.IsDouble() && !representation.IsDouble());
3210 }
3211 } else {
3212 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kField, old_details.location());
3213 FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(*old_map, old_details);
3214 value = handle(object->RawFastPropertyAt(isolate, index), isolate);
3215 if (!old_representation.IsDouble() && representation.IsDouble()) {
3216 DCHECK_IMPLIES(old_representation.IsNone(),
3217 IsUninitialized(*value, isolate));
3218 value = Object::NewStorageFor(isolate, value, representation);
3219 } else if (old_representation.IsDouble() && !representation.IsDouble()) {
3220 value = Object::WrapForRead(isolate, Cast<JSAny>(value),
3221 old_representation);
3222 }
3223 }
3224 DCHECK(!(representation.IsDouble() && IsSmi(*value)));
3225 int target_index = new_descriptors->GetFieldIndex(i);
3226 if (target_index < inobject) {
3227 inobject_props->set(target_index, *value);
3228 } else {
3229 array->set(target_index - inobject, *value);
3230 }
3231 }
3232
3233 for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(old_nof, new_nof)) {
3234 PropertyDetails details = new_descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3235 if (details.location() != PropertyLocation::kField) continue;
3236 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
3237 DirectHandle<Object> value;
3238 if (details.representation().IsDouble()) {
3239 value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3240 } else {
3241 value = isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value();
3242 }
3243 int target_index = new_descriptors->GetFieldIndex(i);
3244 if (target_index < inobject) {
3245 inobject_props->set(target_index, *value);
3246 } else {
3247 array->set(target_index - inobject, *value);
3248 }
3249 }
3250
3251 // From here on we cannot fail and we shouldn't GC anymore.
3252 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3253
3254 Heap* heap = isolate->heap();
3255
3256 // Copy (real) inobject properties. If necessary, stop at number_of_fields to
3257 // avoid overwriting |one_pointer_filler_map|.
3258 int limit = std::min(inobject, number_of_fields);
3259 for (int i = 0; i < limit; i++) {
3260 FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(*new_map, i);
3261 Tagged<Object> value = inobject_props->get(i);
3262 object->FastPropertyAtPut(index, value);
3263 }
3264
3265 object->SetProperties(*array);
3266
3267 // Create filler object past the new instance size.
3268 int old_instance_size = old_map->instance_size();
3269 int new_instance_size = new_map->instance_size();
3270 int instance_size_delta = old_instance_size - new_instance_size;
3271 DCHECK_GE(instance_size_delta, 0);
3272
3273 if (instance_size_delta > 0) {
3274 heap->NotifyObjectSizeChange(*object, old_instance_size, new_instance_size,
3275 ClearRecordedSlots::kYes);
3276 }
3277
3278 // We are storing the new map using release store after creating a filler for
3279 // the left-over space to avoid races with the sweeper thread.
3280 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3281}
3282
3283void MigrateFastToSlow(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3284 DirectHandle<Map> new_map,
3285 int expected_additional_properties) {
3286 // The global object is always normalized.
3287 DCHECK(!IsJSGlobalObject(*object, isolate));
3288 // JSGlobalProxy must never be normalized
3289 DCHECK(!IsJSGlobalProxy(*object, isolate));
3290
3291 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_map->is_prototype_map(),
3292 Map::IsPrototypeChainInvalidated(*new_map));
3293
3294 HandleScope scope(isolate);
3295 DirectHandle<Map> map(object->map(isolate), isolate);
3296
3297 // Allocate new content.
3298 int real_size = map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
3299 int property_count = real_size;
3300 if (expected_additional_properties > 0) {
3301 property_count += expected_additional_properties;
3302 } else {
3303 // Make space for two more properties.
3304 constexpr int initial_capacity = PropertyDictionary::kInitialCapacity;
3305 property_count += initial_capacity;
3306 }
3307
3308 DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary;
3309 DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> ord_dictionary;
3310 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3311 ord_dictionary = isolate->factory()->NewSwissNameDictionary(property_count);
3312 } else {
3313 dictionary = isolate->factory()->NewNameDictionary(property_count);
3314 }
3315
3316 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descs(map->instance_descriptors(isolate),
3317 isolate);
3318 for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(real_size)) {
3319 PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
3320 DirectHandle<Name> key(descs->GetKey(isolate, i), isolate);
3321 DirectHandle<Object> value;
3322 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
3323 FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(*map, details);
3324 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
3325 value =
3326 direct_handle(object->RawFastPropertyAt(isolate, index), isolate);
3327 if (details.representation().IsDouble()) {
3328 DCHECK(IsHeapNumber(*value, isolate));
3329 double old_value = Cast<HeapNumber>(value)->value();
3330 value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumber(old_value);
3331 }
3332 } else {
3333 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
3334 value =
3335 direct_handle(object->RawFastPropertyAt(isolate, index), isolate);
3336 }
3337
3338 } else {
3339 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kDescriptor, details.location());
3340 value = direct_handle(descs->GetStrongValue(isolate, i), isolate);
3341 }
3342 DCHECK(!value.is_null());
3343 PropertyConstness constness = V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL
3344 ? details.constness()
3345 : PropertyConstness::kMutable;
3346 PropertyDetails d(details.kind(), details.attributes(), constness);
3347
3348 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3349 ord_dictionary =
3350 SwissNameDictionary::Add(isolate, ord_dictionary, key, value, d);
3351 } else {
3352 dictionary = NameDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, key, value, d);
3353 }
3354 }
3355
3356 if constexpr (!V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3357 // Copy the next enumeration index from instance descriptor.
3358 dictionary->set_next_enumeration_index(real_size + 1);
3359 // TODO(pthier): Add flags to swiss dictionaries.
3360 dictionary->set_may_have_interesting_properties(
3361 map->may_have_interesting_properties());
3362 }
3363
3364 // From here on we cannot fail and we shouldn't GC anymore.
3365 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3366
3367 Heap* heap = isolate->heap();
3368
3369 // Resize the object in the heap if necessary.
3370 int old_instance_size = map->instance_size();
3371 int new_instance_size = new_map->instance_size();
3372 int instance_size_delta = old_instance_size - new_instance_size;
3373 DCHECK_GE(instance_size_delta, 0);
3374
3375 if (instance_size_delta > 0) {
3376 heap->NotifyObjectSizeChange(*object, old_instance_size, new_instance_size,
3377 ClearRecordedSlots::kYes);
3378 }
3379
3380 // We are storing the new map using release store after creating a filler for
3381 // the left-over space to avoid races with the sweeper thread.
3382 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3383
3384 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3385 object->SetProperties(*ord_dictionary);
3386 } else {
3387 object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
3388 }
3389
3390 // Ensure that in-object space of slow-mode object does not contain random
3391 // garbage.
3392 int inobject_properties = new_map->GetInObjectProperties();
3393 if (inobject_properties) {
3394 for (int i = 0; i < inobject_properties; i++) {
3395 FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(*new_map, i);
3396 object->FastPropertyAtPut(index, Smi::zero());
3397 }
3398 }
3399
3400#ifdef DEBUG
3401 if (v8_flags.trace_normalization) {
3402 StdoutStream os;
3403 os << "Object properties have been normalized:\n";
3404 Print(*object, os);
3405 }
3406#endif
3407}
3408
3409} // namespace
3410
3411void JSObject::MigrateToMap(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3412 DirectHandle<Map> new_map,
3413 int expected_additional_properties) {
3414 if (object->map(isolate) == *new_map) return;
3415 DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(isolate), isolate);
3416 NotifyMapChange(old_map, new_map, isolate);
3417
3418 if (old_map->is_dictionary_map()) {
3419 // For slow-to-fast migrations JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast()
3420 // must be used instead.
3421 CHECK(new_map->is_dictionary_map());
3422
3423 // Slow-to-slow migration is trivial.
3424 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3425 } else if (!new_map->is_dictionary_map()) {
3426 MigrateFastToFast(isolate, object, new_map);
3427 if (old_map->is_prototype_map()) {
3428 DCHECK(!old_map->is_stable());
3429 DCHECK(new_map->is_stable());
3430 DCHECK(new_map->owns_descriptors());
3431 DCHECK(old_map->owns_descriptors());
3432 // Transfer ownership to the new map. Keep the descriptor pointer of the
3433 // old map intact because the concurrent marker might be iterating the
3434 // object with the old map.
3435 old_map->set_owns_descriptors(false);
3436 DCHECK(old_map->is_abandoned_prototype_map());
3437 // Ensure that no transition was inserted for prototype migrations.
3438 DCHECK_EQ(0,
3439 TransitionsAccessor(isolate, *old_map).NumberOfTransitions());
3440 DCHECK(IsUndefined(new_map->GetBackPointer(isolate), isolate));
3441 DCHECK(object->map(isolate) != *old_map);
3442 }
3443 } else {
3444 MigrateFastToSlow(isolate, object, new_map, expected_additional_properties);
3445 }
3446
3447 // Careful: Don't allocate here!
3448 // For some callers of this method, |object| might be in an inconsistent
3449 // state now: the new map might have a new elements_kind, but the object's
3450 // elements pointer hasn't been updated yet. Callers will fix this, but in
3451 // the meantime, (indirectly) calling JSObjectVerify() must be avoided.
3452 // When adding code here, add a DisallowGarbageCollection too.
3453}
3454
3455void JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(Isolate* isolate,
3456 DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3457 DirectHandle<JSPrototype> proto) {
3458 // object.__proto__ = proto;
3459 DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate);
3460 DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::Copy(isolate, old_map, "ForceSetPrototype");
3461 Map::SetPrototype(isolate, new_map, proto);
3462 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
3463}
3464
3465Maybe<InterceptorResult> JSObject::SetPropertyWithInterceptor(
3466 LookupIterator* it, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
3467 DirectHandle<Object> value) {
3468 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR, it->state());
3469 return SetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(it, it->GetInterceptor(),
3470 should_throw, value);
3471}
3472
3473Handle<Map> JSObject::GetElementsTransitionMap(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3474 ElementsKind to_kind) {
3475 Handle<Map> map(object->map(), object->GetIsolate());
3476 return Map::TransitionElementsTo(object->GetIsolate(), map, to_kind);
3477}
3478
3479void JSObject::AllocateStorageForMap(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3480 Handle<Map> map) {
3481 DCHECK(object->map()->GetInObjectProperties() ==
3482 map->GetInObjectProperties());
3483 ElementsKind obj_kind = object->map()->elements_kind();
3484 ElementsKind map_kind = map->elements_kind();
3485 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
3486 if (map_kind != obj_kind) {
3487 ElementsKind to_kind = GetMoreGeneralElementsKind(map_kind, obj_kind);
3488 if (IsDictionaryElementsKind(obj_kind)) {
3489 to_kind = obj_kind;
3490 }
3491 if (IsDictionaryElementsKind(to_kind)) {
3492 NormalizeElements(object);
3493 } else {
3494 TransitionElementsKind(object, to_kind);
3495 }
3496 map = MapUpdater{isolate, map}.ReconfigureElementsKind(to_kind);
3497 }
3498 int number_of_fields = map->NumberOfFields(ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
3499 int inobject = map->GetInObjectProperties();
3500 int unused = map->UnusedPropertyFields();
3501 int total_size = number_of_fields + unused;
3502 int external = total_size - inobject;
3503 // Allocate mutable double boxes if necessary. It is always necessary if we
3504 // have external properties, but is also necessary if we only have inobject
3505 // properties but don't unbox double fields.
3506
3507 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descriptors(map->instance_descriptors(isolate),
3508 isolate);
3509 DirectHandle<FixedArray> storage =
3510 isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(inobject);
3511
3512 DirectHandle<PropertyArray> array =
3513 isolate->factory()->NewPropertyArray(external);
3514
3515 for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
3516 PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3517 Representation representation = details.representation();
3518 if (!representation.IsDouble()) continue;
3519 FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(*map, details);
3520 auto box = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3521 if (index.is_inobject()) {
3522 storage->set(index.property_index(), *box);
3523 } else {
3524 array->set(index.outobject_array_index(), *box);
3525 }
3526 }
3527
3528 object->SetProperties(*array);
3529 for (int i = 0; i < inobject; i++) {
3530 FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(*map, i);
3531 Tagged<Object> value = storage->get(i);
3532 object->FastPropertyAtPut(index, value);
3533 }
3534 object->set_map(isolate, *map, kReleaseStore);
3535}
3536
3537void JSObject::MigrateInstance(Isolate* isolate,
3538 DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
3539 Handle<Map> original_map(object->map(), isolate);
3540 DirectHandle<Map> map = Map::Update(isolate, original_map);
3541 map->set_is_migration_target(true);
3542 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, map);
3543 if (v8_flags.trace_migration) {
3544 object->PrintInstanceMigration(stdout, *original_map, *map);
3545 }
3546#if VERIFY_HEAP
3547 if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
3548 object->JSObjectVerify(isolate);
3549 }
3550#endif
3551}
3552
3553// static
3554bool JSObject::TryMigrateInstance(Isolate* isolate,
3555 DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
3556 DisallowDeoptimization no_deoptimization(isolate);
3557 Handle<Map> original_map(object->map(), isolate);
3558 DirectHandle<Map> new_map;
3559 if (!Map::TryUpdate(isolate, original_map).ToHandle(&new_map)) {
3560 return false;
3561 }
3562 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
3563 if (v8_flags.trace_migration && *original_map != object->map()) {
3564 object->PrintInstanceMigration(stdout, *original_map, object->map());
3565 }
3566#if VERIFY_HEAP
3567 if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
3568 object->JSObjectVerify(isolate);
3569 }
3570#endif
3571 return true;
3572}

3575
3576bool TryFastAddDataProperty(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3577 DirectHandle<Name> name, DirectHandle<Object> value,
3578 PropertyAttributes attributes) {
3579 DCHECK(IsUniqueName(*name));
3580 Tagged<Map> map =
3581 TransitionsAccessor(isolate, object->map())
3582 .SearchTransition(*name, PropertyKind::kData, attributes);
3583 if (map.is_null()) return false;
3584 DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
3585
3586 Handle<Map> new_map(map, isolate);
3587 if (map->is_deprecated()) {
3588 new_map = Map::Update(isolate, new_map);
3589 if (new_map->is_dictionary_map()) return false;
3590 }
3591
3592 InternalIndex descriptor = new_map->LastAdded();
3593 new_map = Map::PrepareForDataProperty(isolate, new_map, descriptor,
3594 PropertyConstness::kConst, value);
3595 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
3596 // TODO(leszeks): Avoid re-loading the property details, which we already
3597 // loaded in PrepareForDataProperty.
3598 object->WriteToField(descriptor,
3599 new_map->instance_descriptors()->GetDetails(descriptor),
3600 *value);
3601 return true;
3602}

3605
3606void JSObject::AddProperty(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3607 DirectHandle<Name> name, DirectHandle<Object> value,
3608 PropertyAttributes attributes) {
3609 name = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(name);
3610 if (TryFastAddDataProperty(isolate, object, name, value, attributes)) {
3611 return;
3612 }
3613
3614 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, name, object,
3615 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
3616 CHECK_NE(LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK, it.state());
3617#ifdef DEBUG
3618 uint32_t index;
3619 DCHECK(!IsJSProxy(*object));
3620 DCHECK(!IsWasmObject(*object));
3621 DCHECK(!name->AsArrayIndex(&index));
3622 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> maybe = GetPropertyAttributes(&it);
3623 DCHECK(maybe.IsJust());
3624 DCHECK(!it.IsFound());
3625 DCHECK(object->map()->is_extensible() || name->IsPrivate());
3626#endif
3627 CHECK(Object::AddDataProperty(&it, value, attributes,
3628 Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError),
3629 StoreOrigin::kNamed)
3630 .IsJust());
3631}
3632
3633void JSObject::AddProperty(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3634 const char* name, DirectHandle<Object> value,
3635 PropertyAttributes attributes) {
3636 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, object,
3637 isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name), value,
3638 attributes);
3639}
3640
3641// Reconfigures a property to a data property with attributes, even if it is not
3642// reconfigurable.
3643// Requires a LookupIterator that does not look at the prototype chain beyond
3644// hidden prototypes.
3645Maybe<bool> JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
3646 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
3647 PropertyAttributes attributes, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
3648 AccessorInfoHandling handling, EnforceDefineSemantics semantics,
3649 StoreOrigin store_origin) {
3650 it->UpdateProtector();
3651
3652 for (;; it->Next()) {
3653 switch (it->state()) {
3654 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
3655 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
3656 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
3657 UNREACHABLE();
3658
3659 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
3660 if (!it->HasAccess()) {
3661 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
3662 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3663 isolate,
3664 isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it->GetHolder<JSObject>()),
3665 Nothing<bool>());
3666 UNREACHABLE();
3667 }
3668 continue;
3669
3670 // If there's an interceptor, try to store the property with the
3671 // interceptor.
3672 // In case of success, the attributes will have been reset to the default
3673 // attributes of the interceptor, rather than the incoming attributes.
3674 //
3675 // TODO(verwaest): JSProxy afterwards verify the attributes that the
3676 // JSProxy claims it has, and verifies that they are compatible. If not,
3677 // they throw. Here we should do the same.
3678 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
3679 InterceptorResult result;
3680 if (semantics == EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine) {
3681 PropertyDescriptor descriptor;
3682 descriptor.set_configurable((attributes & DONT_DELETE) != 0);
3683 descriptor.set_enumerable((attributes & DONT_ENUM) != 0);
3684 descriptor.set_writable((attributes & READ_ONLY) != 0);
3685 descriptor.set_value(Cast<JSAny>(value));
3686 if (!DefinePropertyWithInterceptorInternal(it, it->GetInterceptor(),
3687 should_throw, &descriptor)
3688 .To(&result)) {
3689 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
3690 return Nothing<bool>();
3691 }
3692 } else {
3693 DCHECK_EQ(semantics, EnforceDefineSemantics::kSet);
3694 if (handling == DONT_FORCE_FIELD) {
3695 if (!JSObject::SetPropertyWithInterceptor(it, should_throw, value)
3696 .To(&result)) {
3697 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
3698 return Nothing<bool>();
3699 }
3700 } else {
3701 result = InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted;
3702 }
3703 }
3704 switch (result) {
3705 case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
3706 return Just(false);
3707 case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
3708 return Just(true);
3709 case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
3710 // Proceed lookup.
3711 break;
3712 }
3713
3714 if (semantics == EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine) {
3715 it->Restart();
3716 Maybe<bool> can_define = JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
3717 it->isolate(), it, value, should_throw);
3718 if (can_define.IsNothing() || !can_define.FromJust()) {
3719 return can_define;
3720 }
3721 }
3722
3723 // The interceptor declined to handle the operation, so proceed defining
3724 // own property without the interceptor.
3725 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
3726 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
3727 LookupIterator own_lookup(isolate, receiver, it->GetKey(),
3728 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
3729 return JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
3730 &own_lookup, value, attributes, should_throw, handling, semantics,
3731 store_origin);
3732 }
3733
3734 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
3735 DirectHandle<Object> accessors = it->GetAccessors();
3736
3737 // Special handling for AccessorInfo, which behaves like a data
3738 // property.
3739 if (IsAccessorInfo(*accessors) && handling == DONT_FORCE_FIELD) {
3740 PropertyAttributes current_attributes = it->property_attributes();
3741 // Ensure the context isn't changed after calling into accessors.
3742 AssertNoContextChange ncc(it->isolate());
3743
3744 // Update the attributes before calling the setter. The setter may
3745 // later change the shape of the property.
3746 if (current_attributes != attributes) {
3747 it->TransitionToAccessorPair(accessors, attributes);
3748 }
3749
3750 return Object::SetPropertyWithAccessor(it, value, should_throw);
3751 }
3752
3753 it->ReconfigureDataProperty(value, attributes);
3754 return Just(true);
3755 }
3756 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
3757 return Object::RedefineIncompatibleProperty(
3758 it->isolate(), it->GetName(), value, should_throw);
3759
3760 case LookupIterator::DATA: {
3761 // Regular property update if the attributes match.
3762 if (it->property_attributes() == attributes) {
3763 return Object::SetDataProperty(it, value);
3764 }
3765
3766 // The non-matching attribute case for JSTypedArrays has already been
3767 // handled by JSTypedArray::DefineOwnProperty.
3768 DCHECK(!it->IsElement() ||
3769 !Cast<JSObject>(it->GetReceiver())
3770 ->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements());
3771 // Reconfigure the data property if the attributes mismatch.
3772 it->ReconfigureDataProperty(value, attributes);
3773
3774 return Just(true);
3775 }
3776
3777 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
3778 return Object::AddDataProperty(it, value, attributes, should_throw,
3779 store_origin, semantics);
3780 }
3781 UNREACHABLE();
3782 }
3783}
3784
3785MaybeHandle<Object> JSObject::SetOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
3786 DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<Name> name,
3787 Handle<Object> value, PropertyAttributes attributes) {
3788 DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*value));
3789 LookupIterator it(object->GetIsolate(), object, name, object,
3790 LookupIterator::OWN);
3791 return DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(&it, value, attributes);
3792}
