3817void JSObject::NormalizeProperties(Isolate* isolate,
3818 DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3819 PropertyNormalizationMode mode,
3820 int expected_additional_properties,
3821 bool use_cache, const char* reason) {
3822 if (!object->HasFastProperties()) return;
3823
3824 DirectHandle<Map> map(object->map(), isolate);
3825 DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::Normalize(isolate, map, map->elements_kind(),
3826 {}, mode, use_cache, reason);
3827
3828 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map,
3829 expected_additional_properties);
3830}
3831
3832void JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3833 int unused_property_fields,
3834 const char* reason) {
3835 if (object->HasFastProperties()) return;
3836 DCHECK(!IsJSGlobalObject(*object));
3837 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
3838 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
3839
3840 DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary;
3841 DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> swiss_dictionary;
3842 int number_of_elements;
3843 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3844 swiss_dictionary =
3845 direct_handle(object->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate);
3846 number_of_elements = swiss_dictionary->NumberOfElements();
3847 } else {
3848 dictionary = direct_handle(object->property_dictionary(), isolate);
3849 number_of_elements = dictionary->NumberOfElements();
3850 }
3851
3852 // Make sure we preserve dictionary representation if there are too many
3853 // descriptors.
3854 if (number_of_elements > kMaxNumberOfDescriptors) return;
3855
3856 DirectHandle<FixedArray> iteration_order;
3857 int iteration_length;
3858 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3859 // |iteration_order| remains empty handle, we don't need it.
3860 iteration_length = swiss_dictionary->UsedCapacity();
3861 } else {
3862 iteration_order = NameDictionary::IterationIndices(isolate, dictionary);
3863 iteration_length = dictionary->NumberOfElements();
3864 }
3865
3866 int number_of_fields = 0;
3867
3868 // Compute the length of the instance descriptor.
3869 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
3870 for (int i = 0; i < iteration_length; i++) {
3871 PropertyKind kind;
3872 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3873 InternalIndex index(swiss_dictionary->EntryForEnumerationIndex(i));
3874 Tagged<Object> key = swiss_dictionary->KeyAt(index);
3875 if (!SwissNameDictionary::IsKey(roots, key)) {
3876 // Ignore deleted entries.
3877 continue;
3878 }
3879 kind = swiss_dictionary->DetailsAt(index).kind();
3880 } else {
3881 InternalIndex index(Smi::ToInt(iteration_order->get(i)));
3882 DCHECK(dictionary->IsKey(roots, dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, index)));
3883 kind = dictionary->DetailsAt(index).kind();
3884 }
3885
3886 if (kind == PropertyKind::kData) {
3887 number_of_fields += 1;
3888 }
3889 }
3890
3891 DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate);
3892
3893 int inobject_props = old_map->GetInObjectProperties();
3894
3895 // Allocate new map.
3896 DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::CopyDropDescriptors(isolate, old_map);
3897 // We should not only set this bit if we need to. We should not retain the
3898 // old bit because turning a map into dictionary always sets this bit.
3899 new_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(
3900 new_map->has_named_interceptor() || new_map->is_access_check_needed());
3901 new_map->set_is_dictionary_map(false);
3902
3903 NotifyMapChange(old_map, new_map, isolate);
3904
3905 if (number_of_elements == 0) {
3906 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3907 DCHECK_LE(unused_property_fields, inobject_props);
3908 // Transform the object.
3909 new_map->SetInObjectUnusedPropertyFields(inobject_props);
3910 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3911 object->SetProperties(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array());
3912 // Check that it really works.
3913 DCHECK(object->HasFastProperties());
3914 if (v8_flags.log_maps) {
3915 LOG(isolate, MapEvent("SlowToFast", old_map, new_map, reason));
3916 }
3917 return;
3918 }
3919
3920 // Allocate the instance descriptor.
3921 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
3922 DescriptorArray::Allocate(isolate, number_of_elements, 0);
3923
3924 int number_of_allocated_fields =
3925 number_of_fields + unused_property_fields - inobject_props;
3926 if (number_of_allocated_fields < 0) {
3927 // There is enough inobject space for all fields (including unused).
3928 number_of_allocated_fields = 0;
3929 unused_property_fields = inobject_props - number_of_fields;
3930 }
3931
3932 // Allocate the property array for the fields.
3933 DirectHandle<PropertyArray> fields =
3934 factory->NewPropertyArray(number_of_allocated_fields);
3935
3936 bool is_transitionable_elements_kind =
3937 IsTransitionableFastElementsKind(old_map->elements_kind());
3938
3939 // Fill in the instance descriptor and the fields.
3940 int current_offset = 0;
3941 int descriptor_index = 0;
3942 for (int i = 0; i < iteration_length; i++) {
3943 Tagged<Name> k;
3944 Tagged<Object> value;
3945 PropertyDetails details = PropertyDetails::Empty();
3946
3947 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3948 InternalIndex index(swiss_dictionary->EntryForEnumerationIndex(i));
3949 Tagged<Object> key_obj = swiss_dictionary->KeyAt(index);
3950 if (!SwissNameDictionary::IsKey(roots, key_obj)) {
3951 continue;
3952 }
3953 k = Cast<Name>(key_obj);
3954
3955 value = swiss_dictionary->ValueAt(index);
3956 details = swiss_dictionary->DetailsAt(index);
3957 } else {
3958 InternalIndex index(Smi::ToInt(iteration_order->get(i)));
3959 k = dictionary->NameAt(index);
3960
3961 value = dictionary->ValueAt(index);
3962 details = dictionary->DetailsAt(index);
3963 }
3964
3965 // Dictionary keys are internalized upon insertion.
3966 // TODO(jkummerow): Turn this into a DCHECK if it's not hit in the wild.
3967 CHECK(IsUniqueName(k));
3968 DirectHandle<Name> key(k, isolate);
3969
3970 // Properly mark the {new_map} if the {key} is an "interesting symbol".
3971 if (key->IsInteresting(isolate)) {
3972 new_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
3973 }
3974
3975 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kField, details.location());
3976 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL,
3977 details.constness() == PropertyConstness::kMutable);
3978
3979 Descriptor d;
3980 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
3981 // Ensure that we make constant field only when elements kind is not
3982 // transitionable.
3983 PropertyConstness constness = is_transitionable_elements_kind
3984 ? PropertyConstness::kMutable
3985 : PropertyConstness::kConst;
3986 // TODO(v8:11248): Consider always setting constness to kMutable
3987 // once all prototypes stay in dictionary mode and we are not interested
3988 // in tracking constness for fast mode properties anymore.
3989
3990 d = Descriptor::DataField(
3991 key, current_offset, details.attributes(), constness,
3992 // TODO(verwaest): value->OptimalRepresentation();
3993 Representation::Tagged(), MaybeObjectHandle(FieldType::Any(isolate)));
3994 } else {
3995 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
3996 d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(key, direct_handle(value, isolate),
3997 details.attributes());
3998 }
3999 details = d.GetDetails();
4000 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
4001 if (current_offset < inobject_props) {
4002 object->InObjectPropertyAtPut(current_offset, value,
4003 UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
4004 } else {
4005 int offset = current_offset - inobject_props;
4006 fields->set(offset, value);
4007 }
4008 current_offset += details.field_width_in_words();
4009 }
4010 descriptors->Set(InternalIndex(descriptor_index++), &d);
4011 }
4012 DCHECK_EQ(current_offset, number_of_fields);
4013 DCHECK_EQ(descriptor_index, number_of_elements);
4014
4015 descriptors->Sort();
4016
4017 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4018 new_map->InitializeDescriptors(isolate, *descriptors);
4019 if (number_of_allocated_fields == 0) {
4020 new_map->SetInObjectUnusedPropertyFields(unused_property_fields);
4021 } else {
4022 new_map->SetOutOfObjectUnusedPropertyFields(unused_property_fields);
4023 }
4024
4025 if (v8_flags.log_maps) {
4026 LOG(isolate, MapEvent("SlowToFast", old_map, new_map, reason));
4027 }
4028 // Transform the object.
4029 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
4030
4031 object->SetProperties(*fields);
4032 DCHECK(IsJSObject(*object));
4033
4034 // Check that it really works.
4035 DCHECK(object->HasFastProperties());
4036}
4037
4038void JSObject::RequireSlowElements(Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary) {
4039 DCHECK_NE(dictionary,
4040 ReadOnlyRoots(GetIsolate()).empty_slow_element_dictionary());
4041 if (dictionary->requires_slow_elements()) return;
4042 dictionary->set_requires_slow_elements();
4043 if (map()->is_prototype_map()) {
4044 // If this object is a prototype (the callee will check), invalidate any
4045 // prototype chains involving it.
4046 InvalidatePrototypeChains(map());
4047 }
4048}
4049
4050DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> JSObject::NormalizeElements(
4051 DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
4052 DCHECK(!object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements());
4053 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
4054 bool is_sloppy_arguments = object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements();
4055 {
4056 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4057 Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements = object->elements();
4058
4059 if (is_sloppy_arguments) {
4060 elements = Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(elements)->arguments();
4061 }
4062
4063 if (IsNumberDictionary(elements)) {
4064 return direct_handle(Cast<NumberDictionary>(elements), isolate);
4065 }
4066 }
4067
4068 DCHECK(object->HasSmiOrObjectElements() || object->HasDoubleElements() ||
4069 object->HasFastArgumentsElements() ||
4070 object->HasFastStringWrapperElements() ||
4071 object->HasSealedElements() || object->HasNonextensibleElements());
4072
4073 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
4074 object->GetElementsAccessor()->Normalize(object);
4075
4076 // Switch to using the dictionary as the backing storage for elements.
4077 ElementsKind target_kind =
4078 is_sloppy_arguments ? SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS
4079 : object->HasFastStringWrapperElements() ? SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS
4080 : DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS;
4081 DirectHandle<Map> new_map =
4082 JSObject::GetElementsTransitionMap(object, target_kind);
4083 // Set the new map first to satify the elements type assert in set_elements().
4084 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
4085
4086 if (is_sloppy_arguments) {
4087 Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(object->elements())
4088 ->set_arguments(*dictionary);
4089 } else {
4090 object->set_elements(*dictionary);
4091 }
4092
4093#ifdef DEBUG
4094 if (v8_flags.trace_normalization) {
4095 StdoutStream os;
4096 os << "Object elements have been normalized:\n";
4097 Print(*object, os);
4098 }
4099#endif
4100
4101 DCHECK(object->HasDictionaryElements() ||
4102 object->HasSlowArgumentsElements() ||
4103 object->HasSlowStringWrapperElements());
4104 return dictionary;
4105}
4106
4107Maybe<InterceptorResult> JSObject::DeletePropertyWithInterceptor(
4108 LookupIterator* it, ShouldThrow should_throw) {
4109 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
4110 // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
4111 // interceptor calls.
4112 AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
4113
4114 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR, it->state());
4115 DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor(it->GetInterceptor());
4116 if (IsUndefined(interceptor->deleter(), isolate)) {
4117 return Just(InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted);
4118 }
4119 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
4120 DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
4121 if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
4122 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
4123 Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
4124 Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
4125 }
4126
4127 PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
4128 *holder, Just(should_throw));
4129
4130 v8::Intercepted intercepted =
4131 it->IsElement(*holder)
4132 ? args.CallIndexedDeleter(interceptor, it->array_index())
4133 : args.CallNamedDeleter(interceptor, it->name());
4134
4135 return args.GetBooleanReturnValue(intercepted, "Deleter");
4136}
4137
4138Maybe<bool> JSObject::CreateDataProperty(Isolate* isolate,
4139 DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4140 PropertyKey key,
4141 DirectHandle<Object> value,
4142 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
4143 if (!key.is_element()) {
4144 if (TryFastAddDataProperty(isolate, object, key.name(), value, NONE)) {
4145 return Just(true);
4146 }
4147 }
4148
4149 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN);
4150 Maybe<bool> can_define = JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
4151 isolate, &it, value, should_throw);
4152 if (can_define.IsNothing() || !can_define.FromJust()) {
4153 return can_define;
4154 }
4155
4156 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate,
4157 DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(&it, value, NONE),
4158 Nothing<bool>());
4159
4160 return Just(true);
4161}
4162
4163namespace {
4164
4165template <typename Dictionary>
4166bool TestDictionaryPropertiesIntegrityLevel(Tagged<Dictionary> dict,
4167 ReadOnlyRoots roots,
4168 PropertyAttributes level) {
4169 DCHECK(level == SEALED || level == FROZEN);
4170
4171 for (InternalIndex i : dict->IterateEntries()) {
4172 Tagged<Object> key;
4173 if (!dict->ToKey(roots, i, &key)) continue;
4174 if (Object::FilterKey(key, ALL_PROPERTIES)) continue;
4175 PropertyDetails details = dict->DetailsAt(i);
4176 if (details.IsConfigurable()) return false;
4177 if (level == FROZEN && details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData &&
4178 !details.IsReadOnly()) {
4179 return false;
4180 }
4181 }
4182 return true;
4183}
4184
4185bool TestFastPropertiesIntegrityLevel(Tagged<Map> map,
4186 PropertyAttributes level) {
4187 DCHECK(level == SEALED || level == FROZEN);
4188 DCHECK(!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(map));
4189 DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
4190
4191 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = map->instance_descriptors();
4192 for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
4193 if (descriptors->GetKey(i)->IsPrivate()) continue;
4194 PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
4195 if (details.IsConfigurable()) return false;
4196 if (level == FROZEN && details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData &&
4197 !details.IsReadOnly()) {
4198 return false;
4199 }
4200 }
4201 return true;
4202}
4203
4204bool TestPropertiesIntegrityLevel(Tagged<JSObject> object,
4205 PropertyAttributes level) {
4206 DCHECK(!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(object->map()));
4207
4208 if (object->HasFastProperties()) {
4209 return TestFastPropertiesIntegrityLevel(object->map(), level);
4210 }
4211
4212 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
4213 return TestDictionaryPropertiesIntegrityLevel(
4214 object->property_dictionary_swiss(), GetReadOnlyRoots(), level);
4215 } else {
4216 return TestDictionaryPropertiesIntegrityLevel(object->property_dictionary(),
4217 GetReadOnlyRoots(), level);
4218 }
4219}
4220
4221bool TestElementsIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> object,
4222 PropertyAttributes level) {
4223 DCHECK(!object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements());
4224
4225 ElementsKind kind = object->GetElementsKind();
4226
4227 if (IsDictionaryElementsKind(kind)) {
4228 return TestDictionaryPropertiesIntegrityLevel(
4229 Cast<NumberDictionary>(object->elements()), GetReadOnlyRoots(), level);
4230 }
4231 if (IsTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) {
4232 if (level == FROZEN && Cast<JSArrayBufferView>(object)->byte_length() > 0) {
4233 return false; // TypedArrays with elements can't be frozen.
4234 }
4235 return TestPropertiesIntegrityLevel(object, level);
4236 }
4237 if (IsFrozenElementsKind(kind)) return true;
4238 if (IsSealedElementsKind(kind) && level != FROZEN) return true;
4239 if (IsNonextensibleElementsKind(kind) && level == NONE) return true;
4240
4241 ElementsAccessor* accessor = ElementsAccessor::ForKind(kind);
4242 // Only DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS and SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS have
4243 // PropertyAttributes so just test if empty
4244 return accessor->NumberOfElements(isolate, object) == 0;
4245}
4246
4247bool FastTestIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> object,
4248 PropertyAttributes level) {
4249 DCHECK(!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(object->map()));
4250
4251 return !object->map()->is_extensible() &&
4252 TestElementsIntegrityLevel(isolate, object, level) &&
4253 TestPropertiesIntegrityLevel(object, level);
4254}
4255
4256} // namespace
4257
4258Maybe<bool> JSObject::TestIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate,
4259 DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4260 IntegrityLevel level) {
4261 if (!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(object->map()) &&
4262 !object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements()) {
4263 return Just(FastTestIntegrityLevel(isolate, *object, level));
4264 }
4265 return GenericTestIntegrityLevel(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(object), level);
4266}
4267
4268Maybe<bool> JSObject::PreventExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
4269 DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4270 ShouldThrow should_throw) {
4271 if (!object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements()) {
4272 return PreventExtensionsWithTransition<NONE>(isolate, object, should_throw);
4273 }
4274
4275 if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
4276 !isolate->MayAccess(isolate->native_context(), object)) {
4277 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(object),
4278 Nothing<bool>());
4279 UNREACHABLE();
4280 }
4281
4282 if (!object->map()->is_extensible()) return Just(true);
4283
4284 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*object)) {
4285 PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, object);
4286 if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return Just(true);
4287 DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter)));
4288 return PreventExtensions(
4289 isolate, PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<JSObject>(iter), should_throw);
4290 }
4291
4292 if (object->map()->has_named_interceptor() ||
4293 object->map()->has_indexed_interceptor()) {
4294 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
4295 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotPreventExt));
4296 }
4297
4298 DCHECK(!object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements());
4299
4300 // Normalize fast elements.
4301 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary = NormalizeElements(object);
4302 DCHECK(object->HasDictionaryElements() || object->HasSlowArgumentsElements());
4303
4304 // Make sure that we never go back to fast case.
4305 if (*dictionary != ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_slow_element_dictionary()) {
4306 object->RequireSlowElements(*dictionary);
4307 }
4308
4309 // Do a map transition, other objects with this map may still
4310 // be extensible.
4311 // TODO(adamk): Extend the NormalizedMapCache to handle non-extensible maps.
4312 DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::Copy(
4313 isolate, direct_handle(object->map(), isolate), "PreventExtensions");
4314
4315 new_map->set_is_extensible(false);
4316 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
4317 DCHECK(!object->map()->is_extensible());
4318
4319 return Just(true);
4320}
4321
4322bool JSObject::IsExtensible(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
4323 if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
4324 !isolate->MayAccess(isolate->native_context(), object)) {
4325 return true;
4326 }
4327 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*object)) {
4328 PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, *object);
4329 if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return false;
4330 DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(iter.GetCurrent()));
4331 return iter.GetCurrent<JSObject>()->map()->is_extensible();
4332 }
4333 return object->map()->is_extensible();
4334}
4335
4336// static
4337MaybeHandle<Object> JSObject::ReadFromOptionsBag(
4338 DirectHandle<Object> options, DirectHandle<String> option_name,
4339 Isolate* isolate) {
4340 if (IsJSReceiver(*options)) {
4341 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> js_options = Cast<JSReceiver>(options);
4342 return JSObject::GetProperty(isolate, js_options, option_name);
4343 }
4344 return MaybeHandle<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
4345}
4346
4347template <typename Dictionary>
4348void JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(
4349 Isolate* isolate, ReadOnlyRoots roots, DirectHandle<Dictionary> dictionary,
4350 const PropertyAttributes attributes) {
4351 for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
4352 Tagged<Object> k;
4353 if (!dictionary->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
4354 if (Object::FilterKey(k, ALL_PROPERTIES)) continue;
4355 PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(i);
4356 int attrs = attributes;
4357 // READ_ONLY is an invalid attribute for JS setters/getters.
4358 if ((attributes & READ_ONLY) && details.kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor) {
4359 Tagged<Object> v = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
4360 if (IsAccessorPair(v)) attrs &= ~READ_ONLY;
4361 }
4362 details = details.CopyAddAttributes(PropertyAttributesFromInt(attrs));
4363 dictionary->DetailsAtPut(i, details);
4364 }
4365}
4366
4367template void JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(
4368 Isolate* isolate, ReadOnlyRoots roots,
4369 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary,
4370 const PropertyAttributes attributes);
4371
4372DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> CreateElementDictionary(
4373 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
4374 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> new_element_dictionary;
4375 if (!object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements() &&
4376 !object->HasDictionaryElements() &&
4377 !object->HasSlowStringWrapperElements()) {
4378 int length = IsJSArray(*object)
4379 ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
4380 : object->elements()->length();
4381 new_element_dictionary =
4382 length == 0 ? isolate->factory()->empty_slow_element_dictionary()
4383 : object->GetElementsAccessor()->Normalize(object);
4384 }
4385 return new_element_dictionary;
4386}
4387
4388template <PropertyAttributes attrs>
4389Maybe<bool> JSObject::PreventExtensionsWithTransition(
4390 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, ShouldThrow should_throw) {
4391 static_assert(attrs == NONE || attrs == SEALED || attrs == FROZEN);
4392
4393 // Sealing/freezing sloppy arguments or namespace objects should be handled
4394 // elsewhere.
4395 DCHECK(!object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements());
4396 DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsJSModuleNamespace(*object), attrs == NONE);
4397
4398 if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
4399 !isolate->MayAccess(isolate->native_context(), object)) {
4400 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(object),
4401 Nothing<bool>());
4402 UNREACHABLE();
4403 }
4404
4405 if (attrs == NONE && !object->map()->is_extensible()) {
4406 return Just(true);
4407 }
4408
4409 {
4410 ElementsKind old_elements_kind = object->map()->elements_kind();
4411 if (IsFrozenElementsKind(old_elements_kind)) return Just(true);
4412 if (attrs != FROZEN && IsSealedElementsKind(old_elements_kind)) {
4413 return Just(true);
4414 }
4415 }
4416
4417 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*object)) {
4418 PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, object);
4419 if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return Just(true);
4420 DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter)));
4421 return PreventExtensionsWithTransition<attrs>(
4422 isolate, PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<JSObject>(iter), should_throw);
4423 }
4424
4425 // Shared objects are designed to have fixed layout, i.e. their maps are
4426 // effectively immutable. They are constructed seal, but the semantics of
4427 // ordinary ECMAScript objects allow sealed to be upgraded to frozen. This
4428 // upgrade violates the fixed layout invariant and is disallowed.
4429 if (IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*object)) {
4430 DCHECK(FastTestIntegrityLevel(isolate, *object, SEALED));
4431 if (attrs != FROZEN) return Just(true);
4432 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
4433 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotFreeze));
4434 }
4435
4436 if (object->map()->has_named_interceptor() ||
4437 object->map()->has_indexed_interceptor() ||
4438 (object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements() &&
4439 Cast<JSTypedArray>(*object)->IsVariableLength())) {
4440 MessageTemplate message = MessageTemplate::kNone;
4441 switch (attrs) {
4442 case NONE:
4443 message = MessageTemplate::kCannotPreventExt;
4444 break;
4445
4446 case SEALED:
4447 message = MessageTemplate::kCannotSeal;
4448 break;
4449
4450 case FROZEN:
4451 message = MessageTemplate::kCannotFreeze;
4452 break;
4453 }
4454 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw, NewTypeError(message));
4455 }
4456
4457 DirectHandle<Symbol> transition_marker;
4458 if (attrs == NONE) {
4459 transition_marker = isolate->factory()->nonextensible_symbol();
4460 } else if (attrs == SEALED) {
4461 transition_marker = isolate->factory()->sealed_symbol();
4462 } else {
4463 DCHECK(attrs == FROZEN);
4464 transition_marker = isolate->factory()->frozen_symbol();
4465 }
4466
4467 // Currently, there are only have sealed/frozen Object element kinds and
4468 // Map::MigrateToMap doesn't handle properties' attributes reconfiguring and
4469 // elements kind change in one go. If seal or freeze with Smi or Double
4470 // elements kind, we will transition to Object elements kind first to make
4471 // sure of valid element access.
4472 if (v8_flags.enable_sealed_frozen_elements_kind) {
4473 switch (object->map()->elements_kind()) {
4474 case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
4475 case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
4476 JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(object, PACKED_ELEMENTS);
4477 break;
4478 case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
4479 case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
4480 JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(object, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
4481 break;
4482 default:
4483 break;
4484 }
4485 }
4486
4487 // Make sure we only use this element dictionary in case we can't transition
4488 // to sealed, frozen elements kind.
4489 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> new_element_dictionary;
4490
4491 Handle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate);
4492 old_map = Map::Update(isolate, old_map);
4493 DirectHandle<Map> transition_map;
4494 MaybeDirectHandle<Map> maybe_transition_map =
4495 TransitionsAccessor::SearchSpecial(isolate, old_map, *transition_marker);
4496 if (maybe_transition_map.ToHandle(&transition_map)) {
4497 DCHECK(transition_map->has_dictionary_elements() ||
4498 transition_map->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements() ||
4499 transition_map->elements_kind() == SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS ||
4500 transition_map->has_any_nonextensible_elements());
4501 DCHECK(!transition_map->is_extensible());
4502 if (!transition_map->has_any_nonextensible_elements()) {
4503 new_element_dictionary = CreateElementDictionary(isolate, object);
4504 }
4505 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, transition_map);
4506 } else if (TransitionsAccessor::CanHaveMoreTransitions(isolate, old_map)) {
4507 // Create a new descriptor array with the appropriate property attributes
4508 DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::CopyForPreventExtensions(
4509 isolate, old_map, attrs, transition_marker, "CopyForPreventExtensions");
4510 if (!new_map->has_any_nonextensible_elements()) {
4511 new_element_dictionary = CreateElementDictionary(isolate, object);
4512 }
4513 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
4514 } else {
4515 DCHECK(old_map->is_dictionary_map() || !old_map->is_prototype_map());
4516 // Slow path: need to normalize properties for safety
4517 NormalizeProperties(isolate, object, CLEAR_INOBJECT_PROPERTIES, 0,
4518 "SlowPreventExtensions");
4519
4520 // Create a new map, since other objects with this map may be extensible.
4521 // TODO(adamk): Extend the NormalizedMapCache to handle non-extensible maps.
4522 DirectHandle<Map> new_map =
4523 Map::Copy(isolate, direct_handle(object->map(), isolate),
4524 "SlowCopyForPreventExtensions");
4525 new_map->set_is_extensible(false);
4526 new_element_dictionary = CreateElementDictionary(isolate, object);
4527 if (!new_element_dictionary.is_null()) {
4528 ElementsKind new_kind =
4529 IsStringWrapperElementsKind(old_map->elements_kind())
4530 ? SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS
4531 : DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS;
4532 new_map->set_elements_kind(new_kind);
4533 }
4534 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
4535
4536 if (attrs != NONE) {
4537 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
4538 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*object)) {
4539 DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary(
4540 Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*object)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad),
4541 isolate);
4542 JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(isolate, roots, dictionary,
4543 attrs);
4544 } else if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
4545 DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> dictionary(
4546 object->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate);
4547 JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(isolate, roots, dictionary,
4548 attrs);
4549 } else {
4550 DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary(object->property_dictionary(),
4551 isolate);
4552 JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(isolate, roots, dictionary,
4553 attrs);
4554 }
4555 }
4556 }
4557
4558 if (object->map()->has_any_nonextensible_elements()) {
4559 DCHECK(new_element_dictionary.is_null());
4560 return Just(true);
4561 }
4562
4563 // Both seal and preventExtensions always go through without modifications to
4564 // typed array elements if the typed array is fixed length. Freeze works only
4565 // if there are no actual elements.
4566 if (object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements()) {
4567 DCHECK(new_element_dictionary.is_null());
4568 if (attrs == FROZEN && Cast<JSTypedArray>(*object)->GetLength() > 0) {
4569 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
4570 MessageTemplate::kCannotFreezeArrayBufferView));
4571 return Nothing<bool>();
4572 }
4573 return Just(true);
4574 }
4575
4576 DCHECK(object->map()->has_dictionary_elements() ||
4577 object->map()->elements_kind() == SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS);
4578 if (!new_element_dictionary.is_null()) {
4579 object->set_elements(*new_element_dictionary);
4580 }
4581
4582 if (object->elements() !=
4583 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_slow_element_dictionary()) {
4584 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary(object->element_dictionary(),
4585 isolate);
4586 // Make sure we never go back to the fast case
4587 object->RequireSlowElements(*dictionary);
4588 if (attrs != NONE) {
4589 JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(isolate, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate),
4590 dictionary, attrs);
4591 }
4592 }
4593
4594 return Just(true);
4595}
4596
4597Handle<JSAny> JSObject::FastPropertyAt(Isolate* isolate,
4598 DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4599 Representation representation,
4600 FieldIndex index) {
4601 Handle<JSAny> raw_value(object->RawFastPropertyAt(index), isolate);
4602 return Object::WrapForRead(isolate, raw_value, representation);
4603}

4605Handle<JSAny> JSObject::FastPropertyAt(Isolate* isolate,

4611}

4613// static
4614Handle<Object> JSObject::DictionaryPropertyAt(Isolate* isolate,
4615 DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4616 InternalIndex dict_index) {
4617 DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
4618 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
4619 Tagged<SwissNameDictionary> dict = object->property_dictionary_swiss();
4620 return handle(dict->ValueAt(dict_index), isolate);
4621 } else {
4622 Tagged<NameDictionary> dict = object->property_dictionary();
4623 return handle(dict->ValueAt(dict_index), isolate);
4624 }
4625}
4626
4627// static
4628std::optional<Tagged<Object>> JSObject::DictionaryPropertyAt(
4629 DirectHandle<JSObject> object, InternalIndex dict_index, Heap* heap) {
4630 Tagged<Object> backing_store = object->raw_properties_or_hash(kRelaxedLoad);
4631 if (!IsHeapObject(backing_store)) return {};
4632 if (heap->IsPendingAllocation(Cast<HeapObject>(backing_store))) return {};
4633
4634 if (!IsPropertyDictionary(backing_store)) return {};
4635 std::optional<Tagged<Object>> maybe_obj =
4636 Cast<PropertyDictionary>(backing_store)->TryValueAt(dict_index);
4637
4638 if (!maybe_obj) return {};
4639 return maybe_obj.value();
4640}
4641
4642// TODO(cbruni/jkummerow): Consider moving this into elements.cc.
4643bool JSObject::HasEnumerableElements() {
4644 // TODO(cbruni): cleanup
4645 Tagged<JSObject> object = *this;
4646 switch (object->GetElementsKind()) {
4647 case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
4648 case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
4649 case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
4650 case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
4651 case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
4652 case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
4653 case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS: {
4654 int length = IsJSArray(object)
4655 ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
4656 : object->elements()->length();
4657 return length > 0;
4658 }
4659 case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
4660 case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
4661 case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
4662 case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
4663 case HOLEY_ELEMENTS: {
4664 Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(object->elements());
4665 int length = IsJSArray(object)
4666 ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
4667 : elements->length();
4668 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolate();
4669 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4670 if (!elements->is_the_hole(isolate, i)) return true;
4671 }
4672 return false;
4673 }
4674 case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: {
4675 int length = IsJSArray(object)
4676 ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
4677 : object->elements()->length();
4678 // Zero-length arrays would use the empty FixedArray...
4679 if (length == 0) return false;
4680 // ...so only cast to FixedDoubleArray otherwise.
4681 Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> elements =
4682 Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(object->elements());
4683 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4684 if (!elements->is_the_hole(i)) return true;
4685 }
4686 return false;
4687 }
4688#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) case TYPE##_ELEMENTS:
4689
4690 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE) {
4691 size_t length = Cast<JSTypedArray>(object)->length();
4692 return length > 0;
4693 }
4694
4695 RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
4696#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
4697 {
4698 size_t length = Cast<JSTypedArray>(object)->GetLength();
4699 return length > 0;
4700 }
4701 case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS: {
4702 Tagged<NumberDictionary> elements =
4703 Cast<NumberDictionary>(object->elements());
4704 return elements->NumberOfEnumerableProperties() > 0;
4705 }
4706 case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
4707 case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
4708 // We're approximating non-empty arguments objects here.
4709 return true;
4710 case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
4711 case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
4712 if (Cast<String>(Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(object)->value())->length() >
4713 0) {
4714 return true;
4715 }
4716 return object->elements()->length() > 0;
4717 case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
4718 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4719
4720 case NO_ELEMENTS:
4721 return false;
4722 }
4723 UNREACHABLE();
4724}
4725
4726MaybeHandle<Object> JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(
4727 DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<Name> name,
4728 DirectHandle<Object> getter, DirectHandle<Object> setter,
4729 PropertyAttributes attributes) {
4730 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
4731
4732 PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
4733 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
4734 return DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(&it, getter, setter, attributes);
4735}
4736
4737MaybeHandle<Object> JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(
4738 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> getter,
4739 DirectHandle<Object> setter, PropertyAttributes attributes) {
4740 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
4741
4742 it->UpdateProtector();
4743
4744 while (it->state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
4745 if (!it->HasAccess()) {
4746 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
4747 isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it->GetHolder<JSObject>()));
4748 UNREACHABLE();
4749 }
4750 it->Next();
4751 }
4752
4753 auto object = Cast<JSObject>(it->GetReceiver());
4754 // Ignore accessors on typed arrays.
4755 if (it->IsElement() && object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements()) {
4756 return it->factory()->undefined_value();
4757 }
4758
4759 DCHECK(IsCallable(*getter) || IsUndefined(*getter, isolate) ||
4760 IsNull(*getter, isolate) || IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter));
4761 DCHECK(IsCallable(*setter) || IsUndefined(*setter, isolate) ||
4762 IsNull(*setter, isolate) || IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter));
4763 it->TransitionToAccessorProperty(getter, setter, attributes);
4764
4765 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
4766}
4767
4768MaybeHandle<Object> JSObject::SetAccessor(Handle<JSObject> object,
4769 DirectHandle<Name> name,
4770 DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> info,
4771 PropertyAttributes attributes) {
4772 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
4773
4774 PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
4775 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
4776
4777 // Duplicate ACCESS_CHECK outside of GetPropertyAttributes for the case that
4778 // the FailedAccessCheckCallbackFunction doesn't throw an exception.
4779 while (it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
4780 if (!it.HasAccess()) {
4781 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(object));
4782 UNREACHABLE();
4783 }
4784 it.Next();
4785 }
4786
4787 // Ignore accessors on typed arrays.
4788 if (it.IsElement() && object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements()) {
4789 return it.factory()->undefined_value();
4790 }
4791
4792 Maybe<bool> can_define = JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
4793 isolate, &it, info, Nothing<ShouldThrow>());
4794 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(can_define);
4795 if (!can_define.FromJust()) return it.factory()->undefined_value();
4796
4797 it.TransitionToAccessorPair(info, attributes);
4798
4799 return object;
4800}
4801
4802// static
4803Maybe<bool> JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
4804 Isolate* isolate, LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
4805 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
4806 DCHECK(IsJSObject(*it->GetReceiver()));
4807 if (it->IsFound()) {
4808 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> attributes = GetPropertyAttributes(it);
4809 MAYBE_RETURN(attributes, Nothing<bool>());
4810 if (attributes.FromJust() != ABSENT) {
4811 if ((attributes.FromJust() & DONT_DELETE) != 0) {
4812 RETURN_FAILURE(
4813 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
4814 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed, it->GetName()));
4815 }
4816 return Just(true);
4817 }
4818 // Property does not exist, check object extensibility.
4819 }
4820 if (!JSObject::IsExtensible(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(it->GetReceiver()))) {
4821 RETURN_FAILURE(
4822 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
4823 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed, it->GetName()));
4824 }
4825 return Just(true);
4826}
4827
4828Tagged<Object> JSObject::SlowReverseLookup(Tagged<Object> value) {
4829 if (HasFastProperties()) {
4830 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descs = map()->instance_descriptors();
4831 bool value_is_number = IsNumber(value);
4832 for (InternalIndex i : map()->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
4833 PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
4834 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
4835 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
4836 FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(map(), details);
4837 Tagged<Object> property = RawFastPropertyAt(field_index);
4838 if (field_index.is_double()) {
4839 DCHECK(IsHeapNumber(property));
4840 if (value_is_number && Cast<HeapNumber>(property)->value() ==
4841 Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(value))) {
4842 return descs->GetKey(i);
4843 }
4844 } else if (property == value) {
4845 return descs->GetKey(i);
4846 }
4847 } else {
4848 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kDescriptor, details.location());
4849 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
4850 if (descs->GetStrongValue(i) == value) {
4851 return descs->GetKey(i);
4852 }
4853 }
4854 }
4855 }
4856 return GetReadOnlyRoots().undefined_value();
4857 } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(*this)) {
4858 return Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*this)
4859 ->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad)
4860 ->SlowReverseLookup(value);
4861 } else if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
4862 return property_dictionary_swiss()->SlowReverseLookup(GetIsolate(), value);
4863 } else {
4864 return property_dictionary()->SlowReverseLookup(value);
4865 }
4866}
4867
4868void JSObject::PrototypeRegistryCompactionCallback(Tagged<HeapObject> value,
4869 int old_index,
4870 int new_index) {
4871 DCHECK(IsMap(value) && Cast<Map>(value)->is_prototype_map());
4872 Tagged<Map> map = Cast<Map>(value);
4873 DCHECK(IsPrototypeInfo(map->prototype_info()));
4874 Tagged<PrototypeInfo> proto_info = Cast<PrototypeInfo>(map->prototype_info());
4875 DCHECK_EQ(old_index, proto_info->registry_slot());
4876 proto_info->set_registry_slot(new_index);
4877}
4878
4879// static
4880void JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(DirectHandle<Object> receiver,
4881 WhereToStart where_to_start,
4882 Isolate* isolate) {
4883 if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) return;
4884 for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(receiver),
4885 where_to_start);
4886 !iter.IsAtEnd(); iter.Advance()) {
4887 DirectHandle<Object> current = PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter);
4888 if (!IsJSObjectThatCanBeTrackedAsPrototype(*current)) return;
4889 DirectHandle<JSObject> current_obj = Cast<JSObject>(current);
4890 Tagged<Map> current_map = current_obj->map();
4891 if (current_map->is_prototype_map()) {
4892 // If the map is already marked as should be fast, we're done. Its
4893 // prototypes will have been marked already as well.
4894 if (current_map->should_be_fast_prototype_map()) return;
4895 DirectHandle<Map> map(current_map, isolate);
4896 Map::SetShouldBeFastPrototypeMap(map, true, isolate);
4897 JSObject::OptimizeAsPrototype(current_obj);
4898 }
4899 }
4900}
4901
4902static bool PrototypeBenefitsFromNormalization(Tagged<JSObject> object) {
4903 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4904 if (!object->HasFastProperties()) return false;
4905 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(object)) return false;
4906 // TODO(v8:11248) make bootstrapper create dict mode prototypes, too?
4907 if (object->GetIsolate()->bootstrapper()->IsActive()) return false;
4908 if (V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL) return true;
4909 return !object->map()->is_prototype_map() ||
4910 !object->map()->should_be_fast_prototype_map();
4911}
4912
4913// static
4914void JSObject::OptimizeAsPrototype(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4915 bool enable_setup_mode) {
4916 DCHECK(IsJSObjectThatCanBeTrackedAsPrototype(*object));
4917 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*object)) return;
4918 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
4919 if (object->map()->is_prototype_map()) {
4920 if (enable_setup_mode && PrototypeBenefitsFromNormalization(*object)) {
4921 // This is the only way PrototypeBenefitsFromNormalization can be true:
4922 DCHECK(!object->map()->should_be_fast_prototype_map());
4923 // First normalize to ensure all JSFunctions are DATA_CONSTANT.
4924 constexpr bool kUseCache = true;
4925 JSObject::NormalizeProperties(isolate, object, KEEP_INOBJECT_PROPERTIES,
4926 0, kUseCache, "NormalizeAsPrototype");
4927 }
4928 if (!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL &&
4929 object->map()->should_be_fast_prototype_map() &&
4930 !object->HasFastProperties()) {
4931 JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast(object, 0, "OptimizeAsPrototype");
4932 }
4933 } else {
4934 DirectHandle<Map> new_map;
4935 if (enable_setup_mode && PrototypeBenefitsFromNormalization(*object)) {
4936#if DEBUG
4937 DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(isolate), isolate);
4938#endif // DEBUG
4939 // First normalize to ensure all JSFunctions are DATA_CONSTANT. Don't use
4940 // the cache, since we're going to use the normalized version directly,
4941 // without making a copy.
4942 constexpr bool kUseCache = false;
4943 JSObject::NormalizeProperties(isolate, object, KEEP_INOBJECT_PROPERTIES,
4944 0, kUseCache,
4945 "NormalizeAndCopyAsPrototype");
4946 // A new map was created.
4947 DCHECK_NE(*old_map, object->map(isolate));
4948
4949 new_map = direct_handle(object->map(isolate), isolate);
4950 } else {
4951 new_map = Map::Copy(isolate, direct_handle(object->map(), isolate),
4952 "CopyAsPrototype");
4953 }
4954 new_map->set_is_prototype_map(true);
4955
4956 // Replace the pointer to the exact constructor with the Object function
4957 // from the same context if undetectable from JS. This is to avoid keeping
4958 // memory alive unnecessarily.
4959 Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = new_map->GetConstructorRaw();
4960 Tagged<Tuple2> tuple;
4961 if (IsTuple2(maybe_constructor)) {
4962 // Handle the {constructor, non-instance_prototype} tuple case if the map
4963 // has non-instance prototype.
4964 tuple = Cast<Tuple2>(maybe_constructor);
4965 maybe_constructor = tuple->value1();
4966 }
4967 if (IsJSFunction(maybe_constructor)) {
4968 Tagged<JSFunction> constructor = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
4969 if (!constructor->shared()->IsApiFunction()) {
4970 Tagged<NativeContext> context = constructor->native_context();
4971 Tagged<JSFunction> object_function = context->object_function();
4972 if (!tuple.is_null()) {
4973 tuple->set_value1(object_function);
4974 } else {
4975 new_map->SetConstructor(object_function);
4976 }
4977 }
4978 }
4979 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
4980
4981 if (V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL && !object->HasFastProperties()) {
4982 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
4983 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
4984
4985 auto make_constant = [&](auto dict) {
4986 for (InternalIndex index : dict->IterateEntries()) {
4987 Tagged<Object> k;
4988 if (!dict->ToKey(roots, index, &k)) continue;
4989
4990 PropertyDetails details = dict->DetailsAt(index);
4991 details = details.CopyWithConstness(PropertyConstness::kConst);
4992 dict->DetailsAtPut(index, details);
4993 }
4994 };
4995 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
4996 make_constant(object->property_dictionary_swiss());
4997 } else {
4998 make_constant(object->property_dictionary());
4999 }
5000 }
5001 }
5002#ifdef DEBUG
5003 bool should_be_dictionary = V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL &&
5004 enable_setup_mode && !IsJSGlobalProxy(*object) &&
5005 !isolate->bootstrapper()->IsActive();
5006 DCHECK_IMPLIES(should_be_dictionary,
5007 object->map(isolate)->is_dictionary_map());
5008#endif
5009}
5010
5011// static
5012void JSObject::ReoptimizeIfPrototype(DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
5013 {
5014 Tagged<Map> map = object->map();
5015 if (!map->is_prototype_map()) return;
5016 if (!map->should_be_fast_prototype_map()) return;
5017 }
5018 OptimizeAsPrototype(object);
5019}
5020
5021// static
5022void JSObject::LazyRegisterPrototypeUser(DirectHandle<Map> user,
5023 Isolate* isolate) {
5024 // Contract: In line with InvalidatePrototypeChains()'s requirements,
5025 // leaf maps don't need to register as users, only prototypes do.
5026 DCHECK(user->is_prototype_map());
5027
5028 DirectHandle<Map> current_user = user;
5029 DirectHandle<PrototypeInfo> current_user_info =
5030 Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeInfo(user, isolate);
5031 for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, user); !iter.IsAtEnd(); iter.Advance()) {
5032 // Walk up the prototype chain as far as links haven't been registered yet.
5033 if (current_user_info->registry_slot() != MemoryChunk::UNREGISTERED) {
5034 break;
5035 }
5036 DirectHandle<Object> maybe_proto = PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter);
5037 // This checks for both proxies and shared objects.
5038 //
5039 // Proxies on the prototype chain are not supported. They make it
5040 // impossible to make any assumptions about the prototype chain anyway.
5041 //
5042 // Objects in the shared heap have fixed layouts and their maps never
5043 // change, so they don't need to be tracked as prototypes
5044 // anyway. Additionally, registering users of shared objects is not
5045 // threadsafe.
5046 if (!IsJSObjectThatCanBeTrackedAsPrototype(*maybe_proto)) continue;
5047 auto proto = Cast<JSObject>(maybe_proto);
5048 DirectHandle<PrototypeInfo> proto_info =
5049 Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeInfo(proto, isolate);
5050 Handle<Object> maybe_registry(proto_info->prototype_users(), isolate);
5051 Handle<WeakArrayList> registry =
5052 IsSmi(*maybe_registry)
5053 ? handle(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate->heap()).empty_weak_array_list(),
5054 isolate)
5055 : Cast<WeakArrayList>(maybe_registry);
5056 int slot = 0;
5057 Handle<WeakArrayList> new_array =
5058 PrototypeUsers::Add(isolate, registry, current_user, &slot);
5059 current_user_info->set_registry_slot(slot);
5060 if (!maybe_registry.is_identical_to(new_array)) {
5061 proto_info->set_prototype_users(*new_array);
5062 }
5063 if (v8_flags.trace_prototype_users) {
5064 PrintF("Registering %p as a user of prototype %p (map=%p).\n",
5065 reinterpret_cast<void*>(current_user->ptr()),
5066 reinterpret_cast<void*>(proto->ptr()),
5067 reinterpret_cast<void*>(proto->map().ptr()));
5068 }
5069
5070 current_user = direct_handle(proto->map(), isolate);
5071 current_user_info = proto_info;
5072 }
5073}
5074
5075// Can be called regardless of whether |user| was actually registered with
5076// |prototype|. Returns true when there was a registration.
5077// static
5078bool JSObject::UnregisterPrototypeUser(DirectHandle<Map> user,
5079 Isolate* isolate) {
5080 DCHECK(user->is_prototype_map());
5081 // If it doesn't have a PrototypeInfo, it was never registered.
5082 if (!user->has_prototype_info()) return false;
5083 DCHECK(IsPrototypeInfo(user->prototype_info()));
5084 // If it had no prototype before, see if it had users that might expect
5085 // registration.
5086 if (!IsJSObject(user->prototype())) {
5087 Tagged<Object> users =
5088 Cast<PrototypeInfo>(user->prototype_info())->prototype_users();
5089 return IsWeakArrayList(users);
5090 }
5091 DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype(Cast<JSObject>(user->prototype()), isolate);
5092 DirectHandle<PrototypeInfo> user_info =
5093 Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeInfo(user, isolate);
5094 int slot = user_info->registry_slot();
5095 if (slot == MemoryChunk::UNREGISTERED) return false;
5096 DCHECK(prototype->map()->is_prototype_map());
5097 Tagged<Object> maybe_proto_info = prototype->map()->prototype_info();
5098 // User knows its registry slot, prototype info and user registry must exist.
5099 DCHECK(IsPrototypeInfo(maybe_proto_info));
5100 DirectHandle<PrototypeInfo> proto_info(Cast<PrototypeInfo>(maybe_proto_info),
5101 isolate);
5102 DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> prototype_users(
5103 Cast<WeakArrayList>(proto_info->prototype_users()), isolate);
5104 DCHECK_EQ(prototype_users->Get(slot), MakeWeak(*user));
5105 PrototypeUsers::MarkSlotEmpty(*prototype_users, slot);
5106 if (v8_flags.trace_prototype_users) {
5107 PrintF("Unregistering %p as a user of prototype %p.\n",
5108 reinterpret_cast<void*>(user->ptr()),
5109 reinterpret_cast<void*>(prototype->ptr()));
5110 }
5111 return true;
5112}
5113
5114namespace {
5115
5116// This function must be kept in sync with
5117// AccessorAssembler::InvalidateValidityCellIfPrototype() which does pre-checks
5118// before jumping here.
5119void InvalidateOnePrototypeValidityCellInternal(Tagged<Map> map) {
5120 DCHECK(map->is_prototype_map());
5121 if (v8_flags.trace_prototype_users) {
5122 PrintF("Invalidating prototype map %p 's cell\n",
5123 reinterpret_cast<void*>(map.ptr()));
5124 }
5125 Tagged<Object> maybe_cell = map->prototype_validity_cell(kRelaxedLoad);
5126 if (IsCell(maybe_cell)) {
5127 // Just set the value; the cell will be replaced lazily.
5128 Tagged<Cell> cell = Cast<Cell>(maybe_cell);
5129 Tagged<Smi> invalid_value = Smi::FromInt(Map::kPrototypeChainInvalid);
5130 if (cell->value() != invalid_value) {
5131 cell->set_value(invalid_value);
5132 }
5133 }
5134 Tagged<PrototypeInfo> prototype_info;
5135 if (map->TryGetPrototypeInfo(&prototype_info)) {
5136 prototype_info->set_prototype_chain_enum_cache(Smi::zero());
5137 }
5138
5139 // We may inline accesses to constants stored in dictionary mode prototypes in
5140 // optimized code. When doing so, we install dependencies of group
5141 // |kPrototypeCheckGroup| on each prototype between the receiver's immediate
5142 // prototype and the holder of the constant property. This dependency is used
5143 // both to detect changes to the constant value itself, and other changes to
5144 // the prototype chain that invalidate the access to the given property from
5145 // the given receiver (like adding the property to another prototype between
5146 // the receiver and the (previous) holder). This works by de-opting this group
5147 // whenever the validity cell would be invalidated. However, the actual value
5148 // of the validity cell is not used. Therefore, we always trigger the de-opt
5149 // here, even if the cell was already invalid.
5150 if (V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL && map->is_dictionary_map()) {
5151 // TODO(11527): pass Isolate as an argument.
5152 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolateFromWritableObject(map);
5153 DependentCode::DeoptimizeDependencyGroups(
5154 isolate, map, DependentCode::kPrototypeCheckGroup);
5155 }
5156}
5157
5158void InvalidatePrototypeChainsInternal(Tagged<Map> map) {
5159 // We handle linear prototype chains by looping, and multiple children
5160 // by recursion, in order to reduce the likelihood of running into stack
5161 // overflows. So, conceptually, the outer loop iterates the depth of the
5162 // prototype tree, and the inner loop iterates the breadth of a node.
5163 Tagged<Map> next_map;
5164 for (; !map.is_null(); map = next_map, next_map = Map()) {
5165 InvalidateOnePrototypeValidityCellInternal(map);
5166
5167 Tagged<PrototypeInfo> proto_info;
5168 if (!map->TryGetPrototypeInfo(&proto_info)) return;
5169 if (!IsWeakArrayList(proto_info->prototype_users())) {
5170 return;
5171 }
5172 Tagged<WeakArrayList> prototype_users =
5173 Cast<WeakArrayList>(proto_info->prototype_users());
5174 // For now, only maps register themselves as users.
5175 for (int i = PrototypeUsers::kFirstIndex; i < prototype_users->length();
5176 ++i) {
5177 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
5178 if (prototype_users->Get(i).GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&heap_object) &&
5179 IsMap(heap_object)) {
5180 // Walk the prototype chain (backwards, towards leaf objects) if
5181 // necessary.
5182 if (next_map.is_null()) {
5183 next_map = Cast<Map>(heap_object);
5184 } else {
5185 InvalidatePrototypeChainsInternal(Cast<Map>(heap_object));
5186 }
5187 }
5188 }
5189 }
5190}
5191
5192} // namespace
5193
5194// static
5195Tagged<Map> JSObject::InvalidatePrototypeChains(Tagged<Map> map) {
5196 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5197 InvalidatePrototypeChainsInternal(map);
5198 return map;
5199}
5200
5201// We also invalidate global objects validity cell when a new lexical
5202// environment variable is added. This is necessary to ensure that
5203// Load/StoreGlobalIC handlers that load/store from global object's prototype
5204// get properly invalidated.
5205// Note, that the normal Load/StoreICs that load/store through the global object
5206// in the prototype chain are not affected by appearance of a new lexical
5207// variable and therefore we don't propagate invalidation down.
5208// static
5209void JSObject::InvalidatePrototypeValidityCell(Tagged<JSGlobalObject> global) {
5210 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5211 InvalidateOnePrototypeValidityCellInternal(global->map());
5212}
5213
5214Maybe<bool> JSObject::SetPrototype(Isolate* isolate,
5215 DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5216 DirectHandle<Object> value_obj,
5217 bool from_javascript,
5218 ShouldThrow should_throw) {
5219#ifdef DEBUG
5220 int size = object->Size();
5221#endif
5222
5223 if (from_javascript) {
5224 if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
5225 !isolate->MayAccess(isolate->native_context(), object)) {
5226 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5227 isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(object), Nothing<bool>());
5228 UNREACHABLE();
5229 }
5230 } else {
5231 DCHECK(!IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object));
5232 }
5233
5234 // Silently ignore the change if value is not a JSReceiver or null.
5235 // SpiderMonkey behaves this way.
5236 DirectHandle<JSPrototype> value;
5237 if (!TryCast(value_obj, &value)) return Just(true);
5238
5239 bool all_extensible = object->map()->is_extensible();
5240 DirectHandle<JSObject> real_receiver = object;
5241 if (from_javascript) {
5242 // Find the first object in the chain whose prototype object is not
5243 // hidden.
5244 PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, real_receiver, kStartAtPrototype,
5245 PrototypeIterator::END_AT_NON_HIDDEN);
5246 while (!iter.IsAtEnd()) {
5247 // Casting to JSObject is fine because hidden prototypes are never
5248 // JSProxies.
5249 real_receiver = PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<JSObject>(iter);
5250 iter.Advance();
5251 all_extensible = all_extensible && real_receiver->map()->is_extensible();
5252 }
5253 }
5254 Handle<Map> map(real_receiver->map(), isolate);
5255
5256 // Nothing to do if prototype is already set.
5257 if (map->prototype() == *value) return Just(true);
5258
5259 bool immutable_proto = map->is_immutable_proto();
5260 if (immutable_proto) {
5261 DirectHandle<Object> msg;
5262 if (IsJSObjectPrototype(*object)) { // is [[Object.prototype]]
5263 msg = isolate->factory()->Object_prototype_string();
5264 } else {
5265 msg = object;
5266 }
5267 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
5268 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kImmutablePrototypeSet, msg));
5269 }
5270
5271 // From 6.1.7.3 Invariants of the Essential Internal Methods
5272 //
5273 // [[SetPrototypeOf]] ( V )
5274 // * ...
5275 // * If target is non-extensible, [[SetPrototypeOf]] must return false,
5276 // unless V is the SameValue as the target's observed [[GetPrototypeOf]]
5277 // value.
5278 if (!all_extensible) {
5279 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
5280 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonExtensibleProto, object));
5281 }
5282
5283 // Before we can set the prototype we need to be sure prototype cycles are
5284 // prevented. It is sufficient to validate that the receiver is not in the
5285 // new prototype chain.
5286 if (Tagged<JSReceiver> receiver; TryCast<JSReceiver>(*value, &receiver)) {
5287 for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, receiver, kStartAtReceiver);
5288 !iter.IsAtEnd(); iter.Advance()) {
5289 if (iter.GetCurrent<JSReceiver>() == *object) {
5290 // Cycle detected.
5291 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
5292 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCyclicProto));
5293 }
5294 }
5295 }
5296
5297 // Set the new prototype of the object.
5298
5299 isolate->UpdateProtectorsOnSetPrototype(real_receiver, value);
5300
5301 DirectHandle<Map> new_map =
5302 v8_flags.move_prototype_transitions_first
5303 ? MapUpdater(isolate, map).ApplyPrototypeTransition(value)
5304 : Map::TransitionToUpdatePrototype(isolate, map, value);
5305
5306 DCHECK(new_map->prototype() == *value);
5307 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, real_receiver, new_map);
5308
5309 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!new_map->is_dictionary_map() && !map->is_deprecated() &&
5310 !IsUndefined(new_map->GetBackPointer()),
5311 size == object->Size());
5312 return Just(true);
5313}
5314
5315// static
5316void JSObject::SetImmutableProto(Isolate* isolate,
5317 DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
5318 DirectHandle<Map> map(object->map(), isolate);
5319
5320 // Nothing to do if prototype is already set.
5321 if (map->is_immutable_proto()) return;
5322
5323 DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::TransitionToImmutableProto(isolate, map);
5324 object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
5325}

5342
5343bool JSObject::WouldConvertToSlowElements(uint32_t index) {
5344 if (!HasFastElements()) return false;
5345 uint32_t capacity = static_cast<uint32_t>(elements()->length());
5346 uint32_t new_capacity;
5347 return ShouldConvertToSlowElements(*this, capacity, index, &new_capacity);
5348}
5349
5350static bool ShouldConvertToFastElements(Tagged<JSObject> object,
5351 Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary,
5352 uint32_t index,
5353 uint32_t* new_capacity) {
5354 // If properties with non-standard attributes or accessors were added, we
5355 // cannot go back to fast elements.
5356 if (dictionary->requires_slow_elements()) return false;
5357
5358 // Adding a property with this index will require slow elements.
5359 if (index >= static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::kMaxValue)) return false;
5360
5361 if (IsJSArray(object)) {
5362 Tagged<Object> length = Cast<JSArray>(object)->length();
5363 if (!IsSmi(length)) return false;
5364 *new_capacity = static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::ToInt(length));
5365 } else if (IsJSArgumentsObject(object)) {
5366 return false;
5367 } else {
5368 *new_capacity = dictionary->max_number_key() + 1;
5369 }
5370 *new_capacity = std::max(index + 1, *new_capacity);
5371
5372 uint32_t dictionary_size = static_cast<uint32_t>(dictionary->Capacity()) *
5373 NumberDictionary::kEntrySize;
5374
5375 // Turn fast if the dictionary only saves 50% space.
5376 return 2 * dictionary_size >= *new_capacity;
5377}
5378
5379static ElementsKind BestFittingFastElementsKind(Tagged<JSObject> object) {
5380 if (!object->map()->CanHaveFastTransitionableElementsKind()) {
5381 return HOLEY_ELEMENTS;
5382 }
5383 if (object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements()) {
5384 return FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS;
5385 }
5386 if (object->HasStringWrapperElements()) {
5387 return FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS;
5388 }
5389 DCHECK(object->HasDictionaryElements());
5390 Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary = object->element_dictionary();
5391 ElementsKind kind = HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS;
5392 for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
5393 Tagged<Object> key = dictionary->KeyAt(i);
5394 if (IsNumber(key)) {
5395 Tagged<Object> value = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
5396 if (!IsNumber(value)) return HOLEY_ELEMENTS;
5397 if (!IsSmi(value)) {
5398 if (!v8_flags.unbox_double_arrays) return HOLEY_ELEMENTS;
5399 kind = HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS;
5400 }
5401 }
5402 }
5403 return kind;
5404}
5405
5406// static
5407Maybe<bool> JSObject::AddDataElement(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5408 uint32_t index, DirectHandle<Object> value,
5409 PropertyAttributes attributes) {
5410 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
5411
5412 DCHECK(object->map(isolate)->is_extensible());
5413
5414 uint32_t old_length = 0;
5415 uint32_t new_capacity = 0;
5416
5417 if (IsJSArray(*object, isolate)) {
5418 CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(Cast<JSArray>(*object)->length(), &old_length));
5419 }
5420
5421 ElementsKind kind = object->GetElementsKind(isolate);
5422 Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements = object->elements(isolate);
5423 ElementsKind dictionary_kind = DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS;
5424 if (IsSloppyArgumentsElementsKind(kind)) {
5425 elements = Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(elements)->arguments();
5426 dictionary_kind = SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS;
5427 } else if (IsStringWrapperElementsKind(kind)) {
5428 dictionary_kind = SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS;
5429 }
5430
5431 if (attributes != NONE) {
5432 kind = dictionary_kind;
5433 } else if (IsNumberDictionary(elements, isolate)) {
5434 kind = ShouldConvertToFastElements(
5435 *object, Cast<NumberDictionary>(elements), index, &new_capacity)
5436 ? BestFittingFastElementsKind(*object)
5437 : dictionary_kind;
5438 } else if (ShouldConvertToSlowElements(
5439 *object, static_cast<uint32_t>(elements->length()), index,
5440 &new_capacity)) {
5441 kind = dictionary_kind;
5442 }
5443
5444 ElementsKind to = Object::OptimalElementsKind(*value, isolate);
5445 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind) || !IsJSArray(*object, isolate) ||
5446 index > old_length) {
5447 to = GetHoleyElementsKind(to);
5448 kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(kind);
5449 }
5450 to = GetMoreGeneralElementsKind(kind, to);
5451 ElementsAccessor* accessor = ElementsAccessor::ForKind(to);
5452 MAYBE_RETURN(accessor->Add(object, index, value, attributes, new_capacity),
5453 Nothing<bool>());
5454
5455 if (IsJSArray(*object, isolate) && index >= old_length) {
5456 DirectHandle<Number> new_length =
5457 isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(index + 1);
5458 Cast<JSArray>(*object)->set_length(*new_length);
5459 }
5460 return Just(true);
5461}
5462
5463template <AllocationSiteUpdateMode update_or_check>
5464bool JSObject::UpdateAllocationSite(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5465 ElementsKind to_kind) {
5466 if (!IsJSArray(*object)) return false;
5467
5468 if (!HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*object)) return false;
5469
5470 if (Heap::IsLargeObject(*object)) return false;
5471
5472 DirectHandle<AllocationSite> site;
5473 {
5474 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5475
5476 Heap* heap = object->GetHeap();
5477 Tagged<AllocationMemento> memento =
5478 PretenuringHandler::FindAllocationMemento<
5479 PretenuringHandler::kForRuntime>(heap, object->map(), *object);
5480 if (memento.is_null()) return false;
5481
5482 // Walk through to the Allocation Site
5483 site = direct_handle(memento->GetAllocationSite(), heap->isolate());
5484 }
5485 return AllocationSite::DigestTransitionFeedback<update_or_check>(site,
5486 to_kind);
5487}
5488
5489template bool
5490JSObject::UpdateAllocationSite<AllocationSiteUpdateMode::kCheckOnly>(
5491 DirectHandle<JSObject> object, ElementsKind to_kind);
5492
5493template bool JSObject::UpdateAllocationSite<AllocationSiteUpdateMode::kUpdate>(
5494 DirectHandle<JSObject> object, ElementsKind to_kind);
5495
5496void JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5497 ElementsKind to_kind) {
5498 ElementsKind from_kind = object->GetElementsKind();
5499
5500 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(from_kind)) {
5501 to_kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(to_kind);
5502 }
5503
5504 if (from_kind == to_kind) return;
5505
5506 // This method should never be called for any other case.
5507 DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(from_kind) ||
5508 IsNonextensibleElementsKind(from_kind));
5509 DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(to_kind) || IsNonextensibleElementsKind(to_kind));
5510 DCHECK_NE(TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, from_kind);
5511
5512 UpdateAllocationSite(object, to_kind);
5513 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
5514 if (object->elements() == ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array() ||
5515 IsDoubleElementsKind(from_kind) == IsDoubleElementsKind(to_kind)) {
5516 // No change is needed to the elements() buffer, the transition
5517 // only requires a map change.
5518 DirectHandle<Map> new_map = GetElementsTransitionMap(object, to_kind);
5519 JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
5520 if (v8_flags.trace_elements_transitions) {
5521 DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elms(object->elements(), isolate);
5522 PrintElementsTransition(stdout, object, from_kind, elms, to_kind, elms);
5523 }
5524 } else {
5525 DCHECK((IsSmiElementsKind(from_kind) && IsDoubleElementsKind(to_kind)) ||
5526 (IsDoubleElementsKind(from_kind) && IsObjectElementsKind(to_kind)));
5527 uint32_t c = static_cast<uint32_t>(object->elements()->length());
5528 if (ElementsAccessor::ForKind(to_kind)
5529 ->GrowCapacityAndConvert(object, c)
5530 .IsNothing()) {
5531 // TODO(victorgomes): Temporarily forcing a fatal error here in case of
5532 // overflow, until all users of TransitionElementsKind can handle
5533 // exceptions.
5534 FATAL(
5535 "Fatal JavaScript invalid size error when transitioning elements "
5536 "kind");
5537 UNREACHABLE();
5538 }
5539 }
5540}
5541
5542template <typename BackingStore>
5543static int HoleyElementsUsage(Tagged<JSObject> object,
5544 Tagged<BackingStore> store) {
5545 Isolate* isolate = object->GetIsolate();
5546 int limit = IsJSArray(object) ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
5547 : store->length();
5548 int used = 0;
5549 for (int i = 0; i < limit; ++i) {
5550 if (!store->is_the_hole(isolate, i)) ++used;
5551 }
5552 return used;
5553}
5554
5555int JSObject::GetFastElementsUsage() {
5556 Tagged<FixedArrayBase> store = elements();
5557 switch (GetElementsKind()) {
5558 case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
5559 case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
5560 case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
5561 case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
5562 case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
5563 case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
5564 case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
5565 return IsJSArray(*this) ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(*this)->length())
5566 : store->length();
5567 case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
5568 store = Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(store)->arguments();
5569 [[fallthrough]];
5570 case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
5571 case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
5572 case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
5573 case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
5574 case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
5575 case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
5576 return HoleyElementsUsage(*this, Cast<FixedArray>(store));
5577 case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
5578 if (elements()->length() == 0) return 0;
5579 return HoleyElementsUsage(*this, Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(store));
5580
5581 case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
5582 case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
5583 case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS:
5584 case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
5585 case NO_ELEMENTS:
5586#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) case TYPE##_ELEMENTS:
5587
5588 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
5589 RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
5590#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
5591 UNREACHABLE();
5592 }
5593 return 0;
5594}

5599 return GetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(it, it->GetInterceptor(), done);
5600}

5638bool JSGlobalProxy::IsDetached() { return !GetCreationContext().has_value(); }
5639
5640void JSGlobalObject::InvalidatePropertyCell(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global,
5641 DirectHandle<Name> name) {
5642 Isolate* isolate = global->GetIsolate();
5643 // Regardless of whether the property is there or not invalidate
5644 // Load/StoreGlobalICs that load/store through global object's prototype.
5645 JSObject::InvalidatePrototypeValidityCell(*global);
5646 DCHECK(!global->HasFastProperties());
5647 auto dictionary =
5648 direct_handle(global->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad), isolate);
5649 InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, name);
5650 if (entry.is_not_found()) return;
5651
5652 DirectHandle<PropertyCell> cell(dictionary->CellAt(entry), isolate);
5653 DirectHandle<Object> value(cell->value(), isolate);
5654 PropertyDetails details = cell->property_details();
5655 details = details.set_cell_type(PropertyCellType::kMutable);
5656 PropertyCell::InvalidateAndReplaceEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry, details,
5657 value);
5658}

5660// static
5661MaybeHandle<JSDate> JSDate::New(DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor,
5662 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> new_target,
5663 double tv) {
5664 Handle<JSDate> result;
5665 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
5666 constructor->GetIsolate(), result,
5667 Cast<JSDate>(JSObject::New(constructor, new_target, {})));
5668 if (DateCache::TryTimeClip(&tv)) {
5669 result->SetValue(tv);
5670 } else {
5671 result->SetNanValue();
5672 }
5673 return result;
5674}
5675
5676// static
5677int64_t JSDate::CurrentTimeValue(Isolate* isolate) {
5678 if (v8_flags.log_timer_events) LOG(isolate, CurrentTimeEvent());
5679 if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) return 4;
5680
5681 // According to ECMA-262, section 15.9.1, page 117, the precision of
5682 // the number in a Date object representing a particular instant in
5683 // time is milliseconds. Therefore, we floor the result of getting
5684 // the OS time.
5685 return V8::GetCurrentPlatform()->CurrentClockTimeMilliseconds();
5686}
5687
5688// static
5689Address JSDate::GetField(Isolate* isolate, Address raw_object,
5690 Address smi_index) {
5691 // Called through CallCFunction.
5692 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5693 DisallowHandleAllocation no_handles;
5694 DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
5695
5696 Tagged<Object> object(raw_object);
5697 Tagged<Smi> index(smi_index);
5698 return Cast<JSDate>(object)
5699 ->DoGetField(isolate, static_cast<FieldIndex>(index.value()))
5700 .ptr();
5701}
5702
5703Tagged<Object> JSDate::DoGetField(Isolate* isolate, FieldIndex index) {
5704 DateCache* date_cache = isolate->date_cache();
5705
5706 if (index < kFirstUncachedField) {
5707 Tagged<Object> stamp = cache_stamp();
5708 if (stamp != date_cache->stamp() && IsSmi(stamp)) {
5709 // Since the stamp is not NaN, the value is also not NaN.
5710 int64_t local_time_ms =
5711 date_cache->ToLocal(static_cast<int64_t>(value()));
5712 SetCachedFields(local_time_ms, date_cache);
5713 }
5714 switch (index) {
5715 case kYear:
5716 return year();
5717 case kMonth:
5718 return month();
5719 case kDay:
5720 return day();
5721 case kWeekday:
5722 return weekday();
5723 case kHour:
5724 return hour();
5725 case kMinute:
5726 return min();
5727 case kSecond:
5728 return sec();
5729 default:
5730 UNREACHABLE();
5731 }
5732 }
5733
5734 if (index >= kFirstUTCField) {
5735 return GetUTCField(index, value(), date_cache);
5736 }
5737
5738 double time = value();
5739 if (std::isnan(time)) return GetReadOnlyRoots().nan_value();
5740
5741 int64_t local_time_ms = date_cache->ToLocal(static_cast<int64_t>(time));
5742 int days = DateCache::DaysFromTime(local_time_ms);
5743
5744 if (index == kDays) return Smi::FromInt(days);
5745
5746 int time_in_day_ms = DateCache::TimeInDay(local_time_ms, days);
5747 if (index == kMillisecond) return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms % 1000);
5748 DCHECK_EQ(index, kTimeInDay);
5749 return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms);
5750}
5751
5752Tagged<Object> JSDate::GetUTCField(FieldIndex index, double value,
5753 DateCache* date_cache) {
5754 DCHECK_GE(index, kFirstUTCField);
5755
5756 if (std::isnan(value)) return GetReadOnlyRoots().nan_value();
5757
5758 int64_t time_ms = static_cast<int64_t>(value);
5759
5760 if (index == kTimezoneOffset) {
5761 return Smi::FromInt(date_cache->TimezoneOffset(time_ms));
5762 }
5763
5764 int days = DateCache::DaysFromTime(time_ms);
5765
5766 if (index == kWeekdayUTC) return Smi::FromInt(date_cache->Weekday(days));
5767
5768 if (index <= kDayUTC) {
5769 int year, month, day;
5770 date_cache->YearMonthDayFromDays(days, &year, &month, &day);
5771 if (index == kYearUTC) return Smi::FromInt(year);
5772 if (index == kMonthUTC) return Smi::FromInt(month);
5773 DCHECK_EQ(index, kDayUTC);
5774 return Smi::FromInt(day);
5775 }
5776
5777 int time_in_day_ms = DateCache::TimeInDay(time_ms, days);
5778 switch (index) {
5779 case kHourUTC:
5780 return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms / (60 * 60 * 1000));
5781 case kMinuteUTC:
5782 return Smi::FromInt((time_in_day_ms / (60 * 1000)) % 60);
5783 case kSecondUTC:
5784 return Smi::FromInt((time_in_day_ms / 1000) % 60);
5785 case kMillisecondUTC:
5786 return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms % 1000);
5787 case kDaysUTC:
5788 return Smi::FromInt(days);
5789 case kTimeInDayUTC:
5790 return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms);
5791 default:
5792 UNREACHABLE();
5793 }
5794
5795 UNREACHABLE();
5796}
5797
5798// static
5799void JSDate::SetValue(double value) {
5800#ifdef DEBUG
5801 DCHECK(!std::isnan(value));
5802 double clipped_value = value;
5803 DCHECK(DateCache::TryTimeClip(&clipped_value));
5804 DCHECK_EQ(value, clipped_value);
5805#endif
5806 set_value(value);
5807 set_cache_stamp(Smi::FromInt(DateCache::kInvalidStamp), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5808}
5809void JSDate::SetNanValue() {
5810 set_value(std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN());
5811
5812 Tagged<HeapNumber> nan = GetReadOnlyRoots().nan_value();
5813 set_cache_stamp(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5814 set_year(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5815 set_month(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5816 set_day(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5817 set_hour(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5818 set_min(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5819 set_sec(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5820 set_weekday(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5821}
5822
5823void JSDate::SetCachedFields(int64_t local_time_ms, DateCache* date_cache) {
5824 int days = DateCache::DaysFromTime(local_time_ms);
5825 int time_in_day_ms = DateCache::TimeInDay(local_time_ms, days);
5826 int year, month, day;
5827 date_cache->YearMonthDayFromDays(days, &year, &month, &day);
5828 int weekday = date_cache->Weekday(days);
5829 int hour = time_in_day_ms / (60 * 60 * 1000);
5830 int min = (time_in_day_ms / (60 * 1000)) % 60;
5831 int sec = (time_in_day_ms / 1000) % 60;
5832 set_cache_stamp(date_cache->stamp());
5833 set_year(Smi::FromInt(year), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5834 set_month(Smi::FromInt(month), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5835 set_day(Smi::FromInt(day), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5836 set_weekday(Smi::FromInt(weekday), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5837 set_hour(Smi::FromInt(hour), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5838 set_min(Smi::FromInt(min), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5839 set_sec(Smi::FromInt(sec), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5840}
5841
5842// static
5843void JSMessageObject::InitializeSourcePositions(
5844 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSMessageObject> message) {
5845 DCHECK(!message->DidEnsureSourcePositionsAvailable());
5846 Script::InitLineEnds(isolate, direct_handle(message->script(), isolate));
5847 if (message->shared_info() == Smi::FromInt(-1)) {
5848 message->set_shared_info(Smi::zero());
5849 return;
5850 }
5851 DCHECK(IsSharedFunctionInfo(message->shared_info()));
5852 DCHECK_GE(message->bytecode_offset().value(), kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset);
5853 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info(
5854 Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(message->shared_info()), isolate);
5855 IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
5856 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureBytecodeArrayAvailable(
5857 isolate, shared_info, &is_compiled_scope, CreateSourcePositions::kYes);
5858 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate, shared_info);
5859 DCHECK(shared_info->HasBytecodeArray());
5860 int position = shared_info->abstract_code(isolate)->SourcePosition(
5861 isolate, message->bytecode_offset().value());
5862 DCHECK_GE(position, 0);
5863 message->set_start_position(position);
5864 message->set_end_position(position + 1);
5865 message->set_shared_info(Smi::zero());
5866}
5867
5868int JSMessageObject::GetLineNumber() const {
5869 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5870 DCHECK(DidEnsureSourcePositionsAvailable());
5871 if (start_position() == -1) return Message::kNoLineNumberInfo;
5872
5873 DCHECK(script()->has_line_ends());
5874 DirectHandle<Script> the_script(script(), GetIsolate());
5875 Script::PositionInfo info;
5876 if (!script()->GetPositionInfo(start_position(), &info)) {
5877 return Message::kNoLineNumberInfo;
5878 }
5879 return info.line + 1;
5880}
5881
5882int JSMessageObject::GetColumnNumber() const {
5883 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5884 DCHECK(DidEnsureSourcePositionsAvailable());
5885 if (start_position() == -1) return -1;
5886
5887 DCHECK(script()->has_line_ends());
5888 DirectHandle<Script> the_script(script(), GetIsolate());
5889 Script::PositionInfo info;
5890 if (!script()->GetPositionInfo(start_position(), &info)) {
5891 return -1;
5892 }
5893 return info.column; // Note: No '+1' in contrast to GetLineNumber.
5894}
5895
5896Tagged<String> JSMessageObject::GetSource() const {
5897 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5898 Tagged<Script> script_object = script();
5899 if (script_object->HasValidSource()) {
5900 Tagged<Object> source = script_object->source();
5901 if (IsString(source)) return Cast<String>(source);
5902 }
5903 return ReadOnlyRoots(GetIsolate()).empty_string();
5904}
5905
5906Handle<String> JSMessageObject::GetSourceLine() const {
5907 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolate();
5908
5909#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5910 if (script()->type() == Script::Type::kWasm) {
5911 return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
5912 }
5913#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5914 Script::PositionInfo info;
5915 {
5916 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5917 DCHECK(DidEnsureSourcePositionsAvailable());
5918 DCHECK(script()->has_line_ends());
5919 if (!script()->GetPositionInfo(start_position(), &info)) {
5920 return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
5921 }
5922 }
5923
5924 Handle<String> src(Cast<String>(script()->source()), isolate);
5925 return isolate->factory()->NewSubString(src, info.line_start, info.line_end);
5926}
